Judas Country is a first person narrative novel by English author Gavin Lyall , first published in 1975 .
The Sense of Beauty is a book on aesthetics by George Santayana .
Accelerando is a 2005 science fiction novel consisting of a series of interconnected short stories by British author Charles Stross .
Three Popes and the Jews is a 1967 book by Pinchas Lapide , a former Israeli Consul to Milan , who at the time of publication was a deputy editor in the Israeli Prime Ministers press office .
Warlords of Atlantis received a Motion Picture Association of America ( MPAA ) rating of PG . It was novelised by Paul Victor .
Star Trek / X - Men is a one - shot comic book crossover , written by Scott Lobdell and published in 1996 .
Caesar Antichrist ( French : César - Antéchrist ) is a short 1895 play by the French writer Alfred Jarry .
The Shadow Club is a book written by Neal Shusterman about two middle school students , Jared Mercer and Cheryl Gannett , who see themselves as the `` second best '' students in their school at the activities that they do best .
The Transall Saga ( also known as Blue Light ) is a 1998 novel by Gary Paulsen .
Woman in Bronze is a novel by Canadian - Lithuanian Antanas Sileika .
Deep Storm is the third solo novel by American author Lincoln Child , published on January 30 , 2007 .
Madmen and Specialists is a play by Wole Soyinka , conceived in 1970 during his imprisonment in the Nigerian Civil War .
Dracula Cha Cha Cha ( re - titled Judgment of Tears in the US ) , is a 1998 novel by British writer Kim Newman .
Ben , in the World is a novel written by Doris Lessing , published in 2000 , in which she stages a parody of the ' objectivity ' of the narrator 's voice .
The Passport ( German : Der Mensch ist ein großer Fasan auf der Welt ) is a novel by Nobel Prize - winning author Herta Müller , published in German in 1986 .
The Death of a Pope is a 2009 novel by prize - winning English writer Piers Paul Read .
Summer in Baden - Baden ( Лето в Бадене ) is a book by a Soviet Jewish writer Leonid Tsypkin .
Maigret in Exile ( French : La Maison du Juge ) is a 1940 detective novel by the Belgian mystery writer Georges Simenon .
The American Boy 's Handy Book is a handbook of activities intended for boys , written by a founder of the Boy Scouts of America , Daniel Carter Beard .
The History of Richard Raynal , Solitary is a historical novel by Robert Hugh Benson , first published in 1906 .
Against All Things Ending is a 2010 fantasy novel by Stephen R. Donaldson .
Confessions of Felix Krull is an unfinished 1954 novel by the German author Thomas Mann .
Petey ( 1998 ) is a children 's novel by Ben Mikaelsen , published in 1998 and set in the 1920s and 1990s .
The Women 's Room is the debut novel by American feminist author Marilyn French , published in 1977 by Jove Books .
Wolf in White Van is the first novel by the American author and singer - songwriter John Darnielle .
`` Nietzsche contra Wagner '' is a critical essay by Friedrich Nietzsche , composed of recycled passages from his past works .
Burglar Bill was written in 1888 by Thomas Anstey Guthrie using the pseudonym F. Anstey , as a recitation .
Murphy 's Herd is the third novel in Murphy series by Gary Paulsen .
Orphans of Chaos is a 2005 science fiction , fantasy novel by John C. Wright .
The Second Sex ( French : Le Deuxième Sexe ) is a 1949 book by the French existentialist Simone de Beauvoir .
The Owl Tree is a novella by Jenny Nimmo which was released in 1997 .
The Canning Season is a young adult novel by American - Canadian author Polly Horvath .
Ayesha 's Rainbow is a 2006 children 's novel written by Rabina Khan about a young Bangladeshi girl who befriends an elderly white neighbour despite escalating racism around them .
This Thing of Darkness was the debut novel of Harry Thompson , published in 2005 only months before his death in November of that year at the age of 45 .
Miss Julie ( Swedish : Fröken Julie ) is a naturalistic play written in 1888 by August Strindberg .
The Unvanquished is a novel by the American author William Faulkner , set in Yoknapatawpha County .
Ramage and the Drumbeat , also published as Drumbeat is an historical novel by Dudley Pope , set during 1796 and 1797 amongst the naval warfare of the French Revolutionary Wars .
`` The Crime and the Glory of Commander Suzdal '' is a science fiction short story by Cordwainer Smith , set in Smith 's `` Instrumentality '' universe .
Passport to Eternity is a short - story collection by J. G. Ballard .
The Flight of Pony Baker is a novel for children , one of the many stories written by William Dean Howells .
Where Troy Once Stood is a book by Iman Wilkens that argues that the city of Troy was located in England and that the Trojan War was fought between groups of Celts .
Tom a Lincoln is a romance by the English writer Richard Johnson , published in two parts in 1599 and 1607 .
Oberon Old and New or Oberon Past and Present is a book containing a new libretto written by Anthony Burgess in 1985 for Carl Maria von Weber 's last opera Oberon ( 1826 ) .
The Mirror Maker is a collection of stories and essays by Italian author Primo Levi originally published in the Italian newspaper La Stampa .
Something to Answer For ( 1969 ) is a novel by the English writer P. H. Newby .
Sudha Parimala is a Sanskrit work on Dvaita philosophy written by Raghavendra Swami .
Those Who Watch is a science fiction novel by Robert Silverberg , first published by Signet in 1967 .
Foundations of Christianity ( German : Der Ursprung des Christentums ) is a 1908 book by Marxist theoretician Karl Kautsky .
The Two Cultures is the first part of an influential 1959 Rede Lecture by British scientist and novelist C. P. Snow .
Touch Not the Cat is a novel by Mary Stewart ; it was first published in 1976 and is one of her best - known works .
`` The Night Flier '' is a horror short story by Stephen King , first published in the anthology Prime Evil :
Gift from the Sea is a book by Anne Morrow Lindbergh first published in 1955 .
Flowers in the Sand ( 2011 ) , the second novel by South African author Clive Algar , has been described by literary critics as `` completely engrossing and superbly written '' and `` a great adventure story '' .
L'Europe galante ( Galant Europe ) is an opéra - ballet in a prologue and four entrées by André Campra , The French text was by Antoine Houdar de la Motte .
Sunshine Sketches of a Little Town is a sequence of stories by Stephen Leacock , first published in 1912 .
The Miracle of Castel di Sangro is an account by American writer Joe McGinniss of the first season Italian club Castel di Sangro Calcio spent in Serie B.
Evil Always Ends is a supernatural detective novella by Joseph Payne Brennan .
' night , Mother is a 1983 play by Marsha Norman about a daughter , Jessie , and her mother , Thelma ( referred to as `` Mama '' in the play ) .
The Tiara Club is a series of children 's books by Vivian French , and published by HarperCollins .
Black - Body Theory and the Quantum Discontinuity , 1894 - 1912 is a 1978 book by Thomas Kuhn , a philosopher and historian of science known for his work The Structure of Scientific Revolutions ( 1962 ) .
Exit the King ( French : Le Roi se meurt ) is an absurdist drama by Eugène Ionesco that premiered in 1962 .
Year 's Best SF 2 ( ISBN 0 - 06 - 105746 - 0 ) is a science fiction anthology edited by David G. Hartwell that was published in 1997 .
Kun nainen hallitsi , rakasti ja vihasi ( Finnish : When a Woman Ruled , Loved and Hated ) is a collection book of historical short stories about European female monarchs by Finnish author Kaari Utrio .
The Corrections is a 2001 novel by American author Jonathan Franzen .
Omega Minor is a 2004 novel by the Belgian writer Paul Verhaeghen .
The Last Love of Arsène Lupin is a posthumous novel written by Maurice Leblanc , rehearsing the later years of his frequent hero , Arsène Lupin .
Raboliot is a French novel , written by Maurice Genevoix , published in 1925 .
The Memoirs of Sherlock Holmes is a collection of Sherlock Holmes stories , originally published in 1894 , by Arthur Conan Doyle .
The Expedition of Humphry Clinker was the last of the picaresque novels of Tobias Smollett , and is considered by many to be his best and funniest work .
There were plans to add two more members to X - Nation 2099 , but the plans were scrapped when Tom Peyer and Humberto Ramos left the book within the first three issues .
Better Than Life is a science fiction comedy novel by Grant Naylor , the collective name for Rob Grant and Doug Naylor , co - creators and writers of the Red Dwarf television series , on which the novel is based .
A Good Marriage is a novella by Stephen King , published in his collection Full Dark , No Stars ( 2010 ) .
Cuckoo 's Egg is a novel by science fiction and fantasy author C. J. Cherryh .
Blue Remembered Earth is a science fiction novel by Welsh author Alastair Reynolds , first published by Gollancz on 19 January 2012 .
A Kind of Loving is a novel by the English novelist Stan Barstow .
Frog and the Birdsong ( Dutch : `` Kikker en het vogeltje '' ) is a 1991 children 's book by Dutch author and illustrator Max Velthuijs .
Ric Hochet is a Franco - Belgian comics series created by Tibet ( drawings ) and André - Paul Duchâteau ( scripts ) .
De Otio ( On Leisure ) is a Latin work by Seneca ( 4 BC--65 AD ) .
Mile 81 is a novella by Stephen King , originally published as an e - book on September 1 , 2011 .
Letters from Lehrer is a play written by Canadian playwright Richard Greenblatt , and performed by him at CanStage , from 16 January to 25 February 2006 .
How Few Remain is a 1997 alternate history novel by Harry Turtledove .
The Lycurgeia ( Ancient Greek : Λυκούργεια , Lykoúrgeia ) is a lost tetralogy by the Athenian dramatist Aeschylus that concerned Thracian Lycurgus ' conflict with Dionysus and its aftermath .
The Tree of Man is the fourth published novel by the Australian novelist and 1973 Nobel Prize - winner , Patrick White .
Crash Deluxe is a postcyberpunk novel by science fiction author Marianne de Pierres and is the third and final Parrish Plessis Novel .
The Year of the Quiet Sun is a 1970 science fiction novel by Wilson Tucker about the use of forward time travel to ascertain future political and social events .
The Burning Dark ( originally titled Shadow 's Call ) is a 2014 sci - fi horror novel by Adam Christopher .
An Essay on Criticism is one of the first major poems written by the English writer Alexander Pope ( 1688 - -1744 ) .
Only the Super - Rich Can Save Us ! is a 2009 fictional work by American political activist Ralph Nader , described by him as a practical utopia , in the style of Edward Bellamy 's 1888 utopian novel Looking Backwards .
Specters of the Dawn ( 1994 ) is a science fiction novel and the third book in the Moreau series by S. Andrew Swann ( aka Steven Swiniarski ) , published by DAW Books .
Fox Bunny Funny is a graphic novel by Andy Hartzell .
In the Lake of the Woods ( 1994 ) is a novel by the American author Tim O'Brien .
Travels with Herodotus is a non - fiction book written by the Polish journalist , Ryszard Kapuściński , published in 2004 and now available in English translation .
Angry White Pyjamas is a book written by Robert Twigger about his time in a one - year intensive program of studying Yoshinkan aikido .
Sex , Slander , and Salvation ( Investigating The Family / Children of God ) was a 1994 book edited by J. Gordon Melton and James R. Lewis , on the Family International .
I Will Fear No Evil is a science fiction novel by Robert A. Heinlein , originally serialised in Galaxy ( July , August / September , October / November , December 1970 ) and published in hardcover in 1970 .
My Big Brother , Boris is a children 's picture book by Liz Pichon , published in 2004 .
The Terminators by Donald Hamilton is a spy novel first published in April 1975 .
`` The Gods of the Copybook Headings '' is a poem published by Rudyard Kipling in 1919 , which , editor Andrew Rutherford said , contained `` age - old , unfashionable wisdom '' that Kipling saw as having been forgotten by society and replaced by `` habits of wishful thinking . ''
Daisy Miller is a novella by Henry James that first appeared in Cornhill Magazine in June--
To Damascus ( Swedish : Till Damaskus ) , also known as The Road to Damascus , is a trilogy of plays by the Swedish playwright August Strindberg .
The Lonestar Legacy were a trilogy of books written by Pastor Gilbert Morris , they are set in the early - mid 19th century in Texas and mix both fiction with non - fiction .
The Real Freshman Handbook ( 1996 ) is a non - fiction book by Jennifer Hanson , which offers `` an irreverent and totally honest guide to life on campus '' .
Big Sur and the Oranges of Hieronymus Bosch is a memoir written by Henry Miller , first published in 1957 , about his life in Big Sur , California , where he resided for 18 years .
Through Alien Eyes is a science fiction novel by Amy Thomson published in 1999 by Ace Books , the sequel to The Color of Distance .
The Load of Unicorn is a children 's historical novel written and illustrated by Cynthia Harnett .
Printemps et autres saisons is the title of a collection of short stories written in French by French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio .
Crown Duel is a 2002 young adult fantasy novel written by American author Sherwood Smith , originally published as two separate books , Crown Duel ( 1997 ) and Court Duel ( 1998 ) .
Wild Ducks Flying Backward is a book by Tom Robbins , published on August 30 , 2005 .
The Firebringer Trilogy is a fantasy series written by Meredith Ann Pierce .
La Fanfarlo is a work by French poet Charles Baudelaire , first published in January 1847 .
The Edible Woman is a 1969 novel that helped to establish Margaret Atwood as a prose writer of major significance .
Tarzan and the Tarzan Twins is a collection of two Tarzan novellas written by Edgar Rice Burroughs for younger readers .
In the Garden of Iden is a 1997 science fiction novel by Kage Baker .
The Exploits of Moominpappa , first published in 1950 and then considerably revised in 1968 under the title Moominpappa 's Memoirs , is the fourth book in the Moomin series by Tove Jansson .
Race and Slavery in the Middle East : an Historical Enquiry is a 1990 book written by the British historian Bernard Lewis .
Handbuch des Schachspiels ( Handbook of Chess , often simply called the Handbuch ) is a chess book , first published in 1843 by Tassilo von Heydebrand und der Lasa .
A Comprehensive Grammar of the English Language ( ISBN 9780582517349 ) is a descriptive grammar of English written by Randolph Quirk , Sidney Greenbaum , Geoffrey Leech , and Jan Svartvik .
The Twilight of Briareus is a science - fiction novel by John Middleton Murry , Jr. , under his pseudonym Richard Cowper .
Explorers of the New Century is the fifth novel by Booker shortlisted author Magnus Mills , published in 2005 .
Nightfall and Other Stories ( 1969 ) is an anthology book compiling twenty previously published science fiction short stories by Isaac Asimov .
`` Les Litanies de Satan '' ( `` The Litanies of Satan '' ) is a poem by Charles Baudelaire , published as part of Les Fleurs du mal .
The Punch and Judy Murders ( also published under the title The Magic Lantern Murders ) is a mystery novel by the American writer John Dickson Carr ( 1906 - -1977 ) , who published it under the name of Carter Dickson .
Saris and the City is a 2010 romantic novel written by Rekha Waheed about a career - driven woman looking for a suitable husband .
Threat Vector is a political thriller novel by Tom Clancy and Mark Greaney published on December 4 , 2012 .
A History of Vodka ( Russian : `` История водки '' , Romanized : Istoriya vodki ) is an academic monograph by William Pokhlyobkin , which was awarded the Langhe Ceretto Prize .
Life Without Principle is an essay by Henry David Thoreau that offers his program for a righteous livelihood .
When the Lion Feeds ( 1964 ) is the debut novel of Rhodesian writer Wilbur Smith .
Stop the Train is a children 's novel by Geraldine McCaughrean , published in 2001 .
Up the Down Staircase is a novel written by Bel Kaufman , published in 1964 , which spent 64 weeks on The New York Times Best Seller list .
Isle of Swords is a pirate novel for young adults by Wayne Thomas Batson , also author of The Door Within Trilogy .
In Praise of Slow ( U.S. title In Praise of Slowness ) is a book by Carl Honoré containing his analysis of the `` Cult of Speed '' , which he claims is becoming the societal standard all over the world .
The Mad Man is a sexually drenched literary novel by Samuel R. Delany , first published in 1994 by Richard Kasak .
Zettels Traum ( ZETTEL 's TRAUM as the author wrote the title ) is a novel published in 1970 by West German author Arno Schmidt .
Toad Rage ( ISBN 0375827633 ) is a book by Australian author Morris Gleitzman .
Are You Dave Gorman ? is the title of a stage show by the British documentary comedian Dave Gorman and the book of the same name , co - written by Gorman and Danny Wallace .
Women Painters of the World , from the time of Caterina Vigri , 1413 - -1463 , to Rosa Bonheur and the present day , assembled and edited by Walter Shaw Sparrow , lists an overview of prominent women painters up to 1905 , the year of publication .
Pigs in Heaven is a 1993 novel by Barbara Kingsolver ; it is the sequel to her first novel , The Bean Trees .
Stranger on the Loose ( 2003 ) is the second book by American author D. Harlan Wilson .
Son of the Mob is a book written by Canadian author Gordon Korman in 2002 .
The Intercom Conspiracy is a novel by British thriller writer Eric Ambler , first published in 1969 .
Motivation , Agency , and Public Policy is a non - fiction book written by the economist Julian Le Grand .
Sons of Fortune is a novel by Jeffrey Archer , published 2002 ( ISBN 1 - 4050 - 2079 - 2 ) .
Distant Lands ( Dalniye Strany , Дальние страны ) is a 1932 novel by the Soviet children 's author Arkady Gaidar .
The Church and the Homosexual is a 1976 book by the Jesuit theologian and priest John J. McNeill .
While America Sleeps is a book by historians Donald Kagan and Frederick Kagan , published September 2000 .
Cowboy Henk is a Belgian absurd humor / surreal humour gag - a - day comic strip series , drawn by Herr Seele and written by Kamagurka .
The Saga of Eric Brighteyes is the title of an epic viking novel by H. Rider Haggard , and concerns the adventures of its eponymous principal character in 10th century Iceland .
Solomon Gursky Was Here is a novel by Canadian author Mordecai Richler first published by Viking Canada in 1989 .
The Unfinished Revolution is a book by Michael Dertouzos , first published in 2001 , that proposes why and how technology should be made to work for humans .
La Cartografía Mallorquina ( The Majorcan cartography ) is a book of essays on the Majorcan portolans written by Professor Julio Rey Pastor with the collaboration of Ernesto García Camarero .
The Morganville Vampires is a series of young adult urban fantasy / vampire novels written by Rachel Caine .
Dreamland Japan is a 1996 book by Frederik L. Schodt published by Stone Bridge Press that was intended as a `` sequel '' to Schodt 's 1983 book Manga !
The Beggar and the Diamond is a re - telling of a Hindu parable written by Stephen King which was published as part of his 1993 short story collection , Nightmares & Dreamscapes .
Memoirs of a Spacewoman is a science fiction novel by Naomi Mitchison , already a noted novelist and poet and sister of the famous biologist J.B.S. Haldane .
The Tenants of Moonbloom is a novel by the Jewish American writer Edward Lewis Wallant ( 1926 - -1962 ) .
The Zero Game is a novel written by Brad Meltzer which follows two senior Congressional staffers who become involved in the clandestine Zero Game .
Unburnable , a novel published in 2006 by HarperCollins / Amistad , was written by the Caribbean author Marie - Elena John ( born in Antigua ) , who was also an Africa Development specialist in New York and Washington , D.C. prior to turning to writing .
The 48 Laws of Power ( 1998 ) is the first book by American author Robert Greene .
Up from the Bottomless Pit and Other Stories ( ISBN 978 - 1 - 59606 - 128 - 6 ) is an original collection featuring a novel and other short literary works by science fiction author Philip José Farmer , edited by Christopher Paul Carey , published in 2007 .
The Distichs of Cato ( Latin : Catonis Disticha , most famously known simply as Cato ) , is a Latin collection of proverbial wisdom and morality by an unknown author named Dionysius Cato from the 3rd or 4th century AD .
`` What the Moon Brings '' is a short story by American horror fiction writer H. P. Lovecraft , written on June 5 , 1922 .
The Lorax is a children 's book written by Dr. Seuss and first published in 1971 .
Destiny Times Three is an alternate timeline 1945 science fiction novel by Fritz Leiber .
You Have Seen Their Faces is a book by photographer Margaret Bourke - White and novelist Erskine Caldwell .
American Flagg ! is an American comic book series created by writer - artist Howard Chaykin , published by First Comics from 1983 to 1989 .
Hey , What 's Wrong with This One ? is a 1969 children 's novel by Maia Wojciechowska .
And Their Children After Them ( ISBN 9780394577661 ) , written by Dale Maharidge and Michael Williamson and published by Pantheon Books in 1989 , won the 1990 Pulitzer Prize for General Non - Fiction .
Herr Lehmann is a German novel by Sven Regener , published in 2001 , adapted for the screen in 2003 .
I , Mona Lisa ( UK title Painting Mona Lisa ) is a historical novel by Jeanne Kalogridis about Lisa Gherardini , the model for Leonardo da Vinci 's painting Mona Lisa .
Star Rangers was a four - issue American science - fiction comic - book series created by writer Mark Ellis and artist Jim Mooney , following the adventures of a military spaceship crew in a 25th - century controlled by corporations .
Mrs Beeton 's Book of Household Management , also published as Mrs Beeton 's Cookery Book is a guide to all aspects of running a household in Victorian Britain , edited by Isabella Beeton .
Dead Fingers Talk , first published in 1963 , was the fifth novel published by Beat Generation author William S. Burroughs .
`` Moving Spirit '' is a science fiction short story by Arthur C. Clarke , first published in 1957 .
Freddy Goes to Florida ( 1927 ) ( formerly published as To and Again ) , is the first of the Freddy the Pig books written by Walter R. Brooks .
The Loss of El Dorado , by the Nobel Prize winner V. S. Naipaul , is a history book about Venezuela and Trinidad .
Odayil Ninnu ( From the Gutter ) is a Malayalam novel written by P. Kesavadev in 1942 .

The Language Instinct is a 1994 book by Steven Pinker , written for a general audience .
On the Jellicoe Road is a young adult novel by Australian novelist Melina Marchetta .
The Concordant Version is an English translation of the Bible compiled by the Concordant Publishing Concern ( CPC ) , which was founded by Adolph Ernst Knoch in 1909 .
A Language Older Than Words is a non - fiction book by Derrick Jensen , first published in 2000 .
The Warden of the Tomb ( Der Gruftwächter ) is an expressionist play by Franz Kafka .

Under the Blood Red Sun is a historical novel by Graham Salisbury , published in 1995 .
Omeros is an epic poem by Caribbean writer Derek Walcott , first published in 1990 .

The Chromium Fence is a 1955 science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick , first published in Imagination magazine .
Croatian God Mars ( Croatian : Hrvatski bog Mars ) , is a collection of short stories , mostly anti - war and social topics by Miroslav Krleža , considered by many as the greatest Croatian writer of the 20th century .
Wives and Daughters is a novel by Elizabeth Gaskell , first published in the Cornhill Magazine as a serial from August 1864 to January 1866 .
Colonialism and Neocolonialism by Jean - Paul Sartre ( first published in French in 1964 ) is a controversial and influential critique of French policies in Algeria .
Spring and All is a volume of poems by William Carlos Williams , first published in 1923 by Robert McAlmon 's Contact Publishing Co.
Manolito Gafotas is a group of children 's novels by the Spanish writer Elvira Lindo .
El espíritu de la música ( Spanish : The spirit of music ) is an 1832 Argentine book by Juan Bautista Alberdi .

Moab Is My Washpot ( published 1997 ) is Stephen Fry 's autobiography , covering the first 20 years of his life .
`` The Swineherd '' ( Danish : Svinedrengen ) is a literary fairy tale by Hans Christian Andersen about a prince who disguises himself as a swineherd to woo an arrogant princess .

The Ringworld series ( 1970 - -2012 ) , by science fiction author Larry Niven , is a part of his Known Space set of stories .
The Waltz of the Toreadors ( La Valse des toréadors ) is a 1951 play by Jean Anouilh .
Null - A Three , usually written Ā Three , is a 1985 science fiction novel by A. E. van Vogt .
L'Abbé C ( 1950 ) was Georges Bataille 's first published novella .
Seven Pillars of Wisdom is the autobiographical account of the experiences of British soldier T. E. Lawrence ( `` Lawrence of Arabia '' ) , while serving as a liaison officer with rebel forces during the Arab Revolt against the Ottoman Turks of 1916 to 1918 .
A Mysterious Affair of Style is a whodunit by Gilbert Adair first published in 2007 .
The Third Epistle to the Corinthians is a pseudepigraphical text under the name of Paul the Apostle .
The Green Futures of Tycho is a 1981 science fiction novel for young audiences by William Sleator .
Sagesse ( literal trans . `` Wisdom '' ) is a volume of French poetry by Paul Verlaine .
Little Women is a novel by American author Louisa May Alcott ( 1832 - -1888 ) , which was originally published in two volumes in 1868 and 1869 .
Men Should Weep ( originally called Quancos Should Dance ) is a play by Ena Lamont Stewart , written in 1956 .
Blackwood Farm ( 2002 ) is one of the more recent books in The Vampire Chronicles and The Mayfair Witches series , written by Anne Rice .
The Quiet Earth is a 1981 science fiction novel ( ISBN 0 - 340 - 26507 - 8 ) by New Zealand writer Craig Harrison .
Doorways in the Sand is a Nebula- and Hugo - nominated science fiction novel with detective fiction and comic elements by Roger Zelazny .
Time of our Darkness is a novel by South African author Stephen Gray .
A Million Open Doors ( 1992 ) is a science fiction novel , the first book of the Thousand Cultures series , by John Barnes .
The Mysterious Affair at Styles is a detective novel by Agatha Christie .
Pop Ćira i pop Spira ( Serbian Cyrillic : Поп Ћира и поп Спира ; `` priest Ćira and priest Spiro '' ) is a 1894 novel by Stevan Sremac .
Kleinzeit is a metaphysical novel by Russell Hoban .
The Operated Jew ( German : Der operirte Jud '' ) is a satirical antisemitic book published by the German physician Oskar Panizza in 1893 .
Popol Vuh 's fortuitous survival is attributable to the Spanish 18th century Dominican friar Francisco Ximénez .
Published in 1983 , Modern Baptists is the universally praised debut novel by American author James Wilcox , and his best known work .
La France juive ( `` Jewish France '' ) , subtitled Essay on Contemporary History , was an antisemitic tract published by Édouard Drumont in 1886 .
In Defense of Anarchism is a 1970 book by Robert Paul Wolff , regarded as a classical work in anarchist scholarship .
Life and Fate ( Russian : Жизнь и судьба ) is a 1959 novel by Vasily Grossman and the author 's magnum opus .
Spring Fire , is a 1952 paperback novel written by Marijane Meaker , under the pseudonym `` Vin Packer '' .
A Good Man Is Hard to Find and Other Stories ( published in England as The Artificial books and Other Tales ) is a collection of short stories by American author Flannery O'Connor .
`` Fragments of Olympian Gossip '' is a poem that Nikola Tesla composed in the late 1920s for his friend , George Sylvester Viereck , an illustrious German poet and mystic .
The Orenda is a historical novel by Canadian author Joseph Boyden .
The Tables Turned is a poem written by William Wordsworth in 1798 and published in his Lyrical Ballads .
On the Halonnesus ( Ancient Greek : Περὶ τῆς Ἀλοννήσου ) is a political oration attributed to the prominent Athenian statesman and orator Demosthenes .
In Dubious Battle is a novel by John Steinbeck , written in 1936 .
A Cruel Bird Came to the Nest and Looked In is a novel by English author Magnus Mills published in 2011 by Bloomsbury .
The Dionysiaca ( Greek : Διονυσιακά ) is an ancient epic poem and the principal work of Nonnus .
On the Concept of Irony with Continual Reference to Socrates ( Danish : Om Begrebet Ironi med stadigt Hensyn til Socrates ) is Søren Kierkegaard 's university thesis paper that he submitted in 1841 .
The Last of the Masters ( also known as Protection Agency ) is a science fiction novelette by Philip K. Dick .
The God of Small Things ( 1997 ) is the debut novel of Indian writer Arundhati Roy .
Who Goes There ? is a science fiction novella by John W. Campbell , Jr. , written under the pen name Don A. Stuart .
Web of Angels is a novel by John M. Ford written in 1980 that investigates the life of a hacker of the Web , an instantaneous communications network that allows some users to retrieve and store data , write programs , and even travel between different human worlds .
Truth and Bright Water is a coming - of - age novel by Thomas King set in the Canadian Prairies on the U.S./Canadian border .
Generations of Winter ( in Russian , Московская сага - Moskovskaya Saga ) is a novel by Russian writer Vasily Aksyonov .
What a Week to Get Real is the eighth part of What a Week series by Rosie Rushton .
Leaven of Malice , published in 1954 , is the second novel in The Salterton Trilogy by Canadian novelist Robertson Davies .
Before I Fall is a 2010 young adult novel written by Lauren Oliver .
Vacuum Diagrams is a collection of science fiction short stories written by Stephen Baxter .
The Consolations of Philosophy ( ISBN 0 - 140 - 27661 - 0 ) is a nonfiction book by Alain de Botton .
The King in Yellow is a book of short stories by American writer Robert W. Chambers , first published by F. Tennyson Neely in 1895 .
Piper in the Woods is a science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick , first published in 1953 in Imagination , and later in The Collected Stories of Philip K. Dick .
The Matlock Paper is the third suspense novel by Robert Ludlum , in which a solitary protagonist comes face to face with a massive criminal conspiracy .
Conan of Cimmeria is a collection of eight fantasy short stories written by Robert E. Howard , L. Sprague de Camp and Lin Carter featuring Howard 's seminal sword and sorcery hero Conan the Barbarian .
The Night Tourist is a children 's fantasy novel by Katherine Marsh , first published in 2008 .
The Arm of the Starfish is a young adult novel by Madeleine L'Engle , first published in 1965 .
The History and Present State of Electricity ( 1767 ) , by eighteenth - century British polymath Joseph Priestley , is a survey of the study of electricity up until 1766 as well as a description of experiments by Priestley himself .
The General 's Wife is a horror short story by Peter Straub .
Megumi - Toons is the popular English title for an autobiographical manga series written by voice actress Megumi Hayashibara .
The Bone Palace by Amanda Downum is a 2010 American fantasy novel centered on the fictional city of death , Erisin .
A Death in White Bear Lake is a true crime book by journalist Barry Siegel , published in 1990 .
Vicky Angel is a children 's book by Jacqueline Wilson , about a young girl 's struggle with her grief over losing her best friend , Vicky .
The Mystery of the Vanishing Treasure is an American juvenile detective novel written by Robert Arthur , Jr. It is the 5th book in the `` Three Investigators '' series .
Blood of Elves ( Polish : Krew elfów ) is the first novel in the Witcher Saga written by Polish fantasy writer Andrzej Sapkowski , first published in Poland in 1994 ( English translation was published in late 2008 ) .
Finding Fish is a 2001 autobiographical book by Antwone Fisher .
The Rasp is a whodunit mystery novel by Philip MacDonald .
Harriet Said ... was the first novel written by Beryl Bainbridge , based on newspaper reports the Parker--
Time and the River is the fourth released novel by author Zee Edgell , appearing in March 2007 .
Nonna Abelarda ( literally Grandma Abelarda ) is a comic fictional character created by Giovan Battista Carpi .
Crowds and Power ( German : Masse und Macht ) is a 1960 book by Elias Canetti , dealing with the dynamics of crowds and `` packs '' and the question of how and why crowds obey power of rulers .
Alfarrábios is a historical novel by the Brazilian writer José de Alencar , first published in 1873 .
No Telephone to Heaven , the sequel to Abeng , is the second novel published by Jamaican - American author Michelle Cliff .
World and Town is a novel by Gish Jen that follows a Chinese American widow and her friendship with a family of Cambodian immigrants .
Confessions of an Economic Hit Man is a partly autobiographical book written by John Perkins published in 2004 .
The Story of Modern Science is a ten - volume book series by Henry Smith Williams , published by Funk and Wagnalls Co. The books , published in 1923 , explained in detail the current technology and scientific methods of the Modern Era .
Ossian 's Ride is a science fiction novel written by astrophysicist Sir Fred Hoyle in 1959 .
The Wool - Pack is a children 's historical novel written and illustrated by Cynthia Harnett , published by Methuen in 1951 .
Z. Marcas is a novelette by French author Honoré de Balzac first published in 1840 .
Dian jang Ta ' Koendjoeng Padam ( Perfected spelling : Dian yang Tak Kunjung Padam , both of which mean The Undying Torch ) is a 1932 novel by Sutan Takdir Alisjahbana .
I Who Have Never Known Men , originally published in French as Moi qui n'ai pas connu les hommes , is a 1995 science fiction novel by Belgian author Jacqueline Harpman .
The Pure Weight of the Heart is Antonella Gambotto - Burke 's first novel and third book .
Paradise Regained is a poem by English poet John Milton , first published in 1671 by John Macock .
Brødre i blodet is a Norwegian novel by Ingvar Ambjørnsen , published in 1996 .
Troubled Sleep ( French : La mort dans l'âme ) is a 1949 novel by Jean - Paul Sartre .
Amaryllis Night and Day is a 2001 novel by Russell Hoban , incorporating elements of magic realism and romance .
Me'am Lo'ez ( Hebrew : מעם לועז‎ ) , initiated by Rabbi Yaakov Culi in 1730 , is a widely studied commentary on the Tanakh written in Ladino - it is perhaps the best known publication in that language .
To Hell You Ride is a 5 issues comic - book series written by Lance Henriksen ( Millennium ( TV series ) , Aliens ( franchise ) , Near Dark ) and Joseph Maddrey ( Nightmares in Red , White and Blue ) , with art by Tom Mandrake , published by Dark Horse Comics , 2012 - 2013 .
Black Juice is the first collection of short stories by Margo Lanagan .
The Angriest Dog in the World is a comic strip created by film director David Lynch .
Miracle in Seville ( 1995 ) is a novel by James A. Michener , the last to be released during his lifetime .
The Knight of the Sacred Lake is a 2001 historical fantasy novel by Rosalind Miles .
Rhode Island on Lovecraft is a 26-page collection of memoirs about H. P. Lovecraft and is edited by Donald M. Grant and Thomas G. Hadley .
The China Study is a book by T. Colin Campbell , Jacob Gould Schurman Professor Emeritus of Nutritional Biochemistry at Cornell University , and his son Thomas M. Campbell II , a physician .
The Invention of Love is a 1997 play by Tom Stoppard portraying the life of poet A. E. Housman , focusing specifically on his personal life and love for a college classmate .
Caucasian days ( French : Jours caucasiens ) is a novel by the French writer of Azeri origin Banine , published in Paris , in 1945 .
The Trial of Henry Kissinger ( 2001 ) is Christopher Hitchens ' examination of alleged war crimes of Henry Kissinger , the National Security Advisor and later United States Secretary of State for Presidents Richard Nixon and Gerald Ford .
The Discovery of the Future is a 1902 philosophical lecture by H. G. Wells that argues for the knowability of the future .
Neat Stuff is an American alternative comic book series created by Peter Bagge and published by Fantagraphics .
An Infinity of Mirrors , first published by Random House in 1964 , was the fifth and most ambitious book by the American satirist and political novelist Richard Condon .
`` Watch Out for This ( Bumaye ) '' is an international 2013 hit single from Major Lazer , a musical project by DJ and music producer Diplo , taken from his album Free the Universe .
Calligrammes , subtitled Poems of Peace and War 1913 - 1916 , is a collection of poems by Guillaume Apollinaire which was first published in 1918 ( see 1918 in poetry ) .
The Falcon 's Malteser is a comic mystery by Anthony Horowitz .
Hitchcock / Truffaut is a 1966 book by François Truffaut about Alfred Hitchcock , originally released in French as Le Cinéma selon Alfred Hitchcock .
The Flying Saucers Are Real by Donald Keyhoe , was a ground - breaking book that investigated numerous encounters between USAF fighters , personnel , and other aircraft , and UFOs between 1947 and 1950 .
Not Wanted on the Voyage is a novel by Canadian author Timothy Findley , which presents a magic realist post - modern re - telling of the Great Flood in the biblical Book of Genesis .
The Two Captains ( Russian : Два Капитана ) is a novel written by Soviet author Veniamin Kaverin between 1938 and 1944 .
The Kill List is a novel by Frederick Forsyth published in 2013 by Random House .
L'Enchanteur ( `` the wizard '' ) is a 1984 novel by the French writer René Barjavel .
`` The Quest for Kalevala '' is an Uncle Scrooge comic book story written and drawn by Keno Don Rosa in 1999 .
The Presentation of Self in Everyday Life is a seminal sociology book by Erving Goffman .
A Shade of Difference ( ISBN 0 - 385 - 02389 - 8 ) is a 1962 political novel written by Allen Drury .
The Last Disaster is a juvenile science fiction novel , the eighteenth in Hugh Walters ' Chris Godfrey of U.N.E.X.A. series .
Sonnet 138 is one of the most famous of William Shakespeare 's sonnets .
The Widow 's Broom is a 1992 children 's novel by the American author Chris Van Allsburg .
Women of Sand and Myrrh is a novel written by Hanan al - Shaykh .
Thinks ... is a 2001 novel by British author David Lodge .
The God Box ( 2007 ) , a novel by Alex Sánchez , focuses on the conflict and friendship between two Christian teenage boys , one openly gay and the other struggling to accept his sexuality .
The Unix Programming Environment , first published in 1984 by Prentice Hall , is a book written by Brian W. Kernighan and Rob Pike , both of Bell Labs and considered an important and early document of the Unix operating system .
Asterix and the Class Act ( French : Astérix et la rentrée gauloise ) is officially the thirty - second album of the Asterix comic book series , by René Goscinny ( stories ) and Albert Uderzo ( illustrations and some stories ) , published in 2003 .
Published in 1974 , Western Attitudes Toward Death from the Middle Ages to the Present was French historian Philippe Ariès '' first major publication on the subject of death .
Gurusagaram ( Eternity of Grace ) is a 1987 novel written by O. V. Vijayan .
Just an Old Sweet Song is a 1976 novel by Melvin Van Peebles , which was later adapted for TV as a special which starred Robert Hooks and Cicely Tyson .
Deadenders is an science fiction comic book series written by Ed Brubaker and published by DC Comics .
The Writing on the Hearth is a children 's historical novel by Cynthia Harnett and illustrated by Gareth Floyd .
Baudolino is a 2000 novel by Umberto Eco about the adventures of a young man named Baudolino in the known and mythical Christian world of the 12th century .
Professor Risley and the Imperial Japanese Troupe is a 2012 book written by Frederik L. Schodt , author of Dreamland Japan and Manga !
Men in the Sun ( Arabic : رجال في الشمس Rijāl fī ash - Shams ) is a novel by Palestinian writer and political activist Ghassan Kanafani ( 1936 - -72 ) , originally published in 1962 .
Ninja High School ( also known as NHS ) is a comic book series created , written , and illustrated by Ben Dunn , and currently published by Antarctic Press .
Marvin K. Mooney Will You Please Go Now ! is a 1972 children 's book by Dr. Seuss .
Trouble with Lichen ( published 1960 ) is a science fiction novel by John Wyndham .
Under the Volcano is a novel by English writer Malcolm Lowry ( 1909 - -1957 ) published in 1947 .
Emperors of the Twilight ( 1994 ) is a biopunk science fiction novel , the second book in the Moreau series by S. Andrew Swann ( aka Steven Swiniarski ) , published by DAW Books .
The Ruby in the Smoke ( 1985 ) is a novel by the English author Philip Pullman .
The Avion My Uncle Flew is a children 's novel by Cyrus Fisher , a pseudonym of Darwin Teilhet .
A Girl and Five Brave Horses is a memoir by Sonora Webster Carver published in 1961 .
Timelike Infinity is a 1992 science fiction book by Stephen Baxter .
`` Jerusalem 's Lot '' is a short story by Stephen King , first published in King 's 1978 collection Night Shift .
Lost Legacy ( 1941 ) is a novella by science fiction writer Robert A. Heinlein .
Rumpole and the Age of Miracles is a 1988 collection of short stories by John Mortimer about defence barrister Horace Rumpole .
John Lonergan ( April 7 , 1839 - -August 6 , 1902 ) was a captain in the Union Army and a Medal of Honor recipient for his actions in the Battle of Gettysburg during the American Civil War .
In an Indian summer to his career , some 20 years after touring England as a schoolboy cricketer , he was named Wisden Cricketer of the Year in 1985 and the Larry Gomes Stadium in Malabar , Arima , is named after him .
Gerhard Grebarsche ( 15 February 1913 -- 11 January 1992 ) was a Hauptscharführer in the Waffen SS who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross on the 24 January 1944 while a platoon commander in the 3rd Company , 2nd SS Panzer Grenadier Regiment , 1st SS Division Leibstandarte SS Adolf Hitler .
Gold Medal and Corot Prize , Salon President of the Salon President of the Society of French Landscape Artists Knight of the Order of the Legion of Honour President of the Jury of the Salon Raymond Wintz died in 1956 and is buried in Montparnasse Cemetery , Paris .
María Carolina Luján ( born May 13 , 1985 in Buenos Aires ) is an Argentine chess player holding the FIDE titles of International Master and Woman Grandmaster .
Karl Kloskowski ( 9 February 1917 -- 23 April 1945 ) was a Hauptsturmführer ( Captain ) in the Waffen - SS who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Carl Gustaf Verner von Heidenstam ( 6 July 1859 -- 20 May 1940 ) was a Swedish poet , novelist and laureate of the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1916 .
Surgeon General James Mouat VC KCB ( 14 April 1815 -- 4 January 1899 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Charles Édouard Guillaume ( 15 February 1861 , Fleurier , Switzerland -- 13 May 1938 , Sèvres , France ) was a Swiss physicist who received the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1920 in recognition of the service he had rendered to precision measurements in physics by his discovery of anomalies in nickel steel alloys .
Tamara Nosova ( Russian : Тамара Макаровна Носова ; 21 November 1927 -- 25 March 2007 ) was a Soviet and Russian actress , who was awarded the title of People 's Artist of Russia in 1992 .
In 1973 , Jean Mandel received the Bavarian Order of Merit .
In 2002 , Gwen Hennessey , along with her sister Dorothy Hennessey , was awarded the Pacem in Terris Award .
Laura Rogule ( born 5 February 1988 , in Riga ) is a Latvian chess player who holds the title of Woman Grandmaster .
Lotte Ulbricht was much decorated by the state and party leadership of East Germany , including in 1959 , 1963 and 1978 the Fatherland Order of Merit , and in 1969 and 1983 the Order of Karl Marx and 1988 the Grand Star of Friendship of Nations .
Carlos Garcia Palermo ( born 2 December 1953 , La Plata ) is an Argentine - Italian chess Grandmaster .
Erwin Böhme ( 29 July 1879 -- 29 November 1917 ) , Pour le Mérite , was a German pilot during World War I. He was born in Holzminden , grew into an athletic sportsman and became a flying ace during the war , credited with 24 victories .
Mirjana Marić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Мирјана Марић ; born January 10 , 1970 in New York , USA ) is a Serbian chess player , who holds the FIDE title of Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) , living in Belgrade , capital of Serbia ( former Yugoslavia ) .
Brigadier General Clement Leslie Smith VC MC ( 17 January 1878 -- 14 December 1927 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Avetik Grigoryan ( Armenian : Ավետիք Գրիգորյան , born January 27 , 1989 ) is an Armenian chess Grandmaster ( 2008 ) .
Carol Emshwiller ( born April 12 , 1921 ) is an American writer of avant garde short stories and science fiction who has won prizes ranging from the Nebula Award to the Philip K. Dick Award .
Massoud Hossaini ( born December 10 , 1981 ) is a photojournalist for Agence France - Presse and winner of the 2012 Pulitzer Prize for Breaking News Photography .
Banarsidas Chaturvedi ( 1892 - 1985 ) was a noted Hindi - language writer , journalist and recipient of Padma Bhushan given by Government of India in 1973 .
Marianna Laba ( Ukrainian : Маріанна Лаба ) , born 7 September 1968 ) is a Ukrainian singer ( soprano ) , Merited Artist of Ukraine , soloist of Lviv State Philharmonic and The Lviv House of Chamber and Organ music .
KH Fakhruddin is regarded as a National Hero of Indonesia .
William Stone Hubbell ( April 19 , 1837 -- August 28 , 1930 ) was a United States Army captain during the American Civil War , and a recipient of the Medal of Honor .
Dominique Pire ( full name : Georges Charles Clement Ghislain Pire ; February 10 , 1910 -- January 30 , 1969 ) was a Belgian Dominican friar whose work helping refugees in post - World War II Europe saw him receive the Nobel Peace Prize in 1958 .
Natalia Edzgveradze ( born 23 July 1975 ) is a Georgian chess Woman Grandmaster and FIDE Trainer ( 2005 ) , currently working in Singapore as a trainer of Intchess Asia Pte Ltd.
János Flesch ( 30 September 1933 -- 9 December 1983 ) was a chess Grandmaster , chess writer and coach , born in Budapest , Hungary .
Captain Louis Fleeming Jenkin , Military Cross & Bar , ( 22 August 1895 -- 11 September 1917 ) was a First World War flying ace credited with 22 victories .
In 1966 Yakov Zak was made People 's Artist of the USSR .
Eleanor Worthington Cox ( born 21 June 2001 ) is a British child actress from Merseyside most known for portraying Matilda Wormwood in Matilda the Musical for which she has won a Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actress along with Cleo Demetriou , Kerry Ingram , and Sophia Kiely .
King was inducted into the National Women 's Hall of Fame in 1990 , and in 2006 , the USTA National Tennis Center in New York City was renamed the USTA Billie Jean King National Tennis Center .
Friedrich - Wilhelm Maes ( 25 November 1913 -- 19 March 1945 ) was a highly decorated Kapitänleutnant in the Kriegsmarine during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Sultan Pepper ( April 22 , 1962 -- October 20 , 2009 ) was an American Emmy Award - winning comedy writer who worked on the Ben Stiller Show and Mad TV .
Grenville Davey ( born 28 April 1961 ) is an English sculptor and winner of the 1992 Turner Prize .
Alfred B. Nietzel ( April 27 , 1921 -- November 18 , 1944 ) is a recipient of the Medal of Honor .
Lionel Greenstreet ( 1889 - 1979 ) was the first officer of the Endurance and a member of the Imperial Trans - Antarctic Expedition of 1914 - 1917 , for which he was awarded the Polar Medal .

Michael A. Mulyar ( born 1978 ) , is an American chess International Master from Westminster , Colorado , and attended Yale University .

XO-4 is a star located approximately 960 light - years away from Earth in the Lynx constellation .
I Zwicky 18 is a dwarf irregular galaxy located about 59 million light years away in the constellation Ursa Major .
HD 60863 is a blue subgiant star located 224 light years away , in the constellation Puppis .
NGC 116 is a possibly lost or non - existent object in the constellation Cetus .
HD 129685 , also known by its Bayer designation c² Centauri ( c² Cen ) , is a star in the constellation Centaurus .
84 Ceti is the Flamsteed designation for a binary star system in the equatorial constellation of Cetus .
GJ 3379 ( Giclas 99 - 49 ) is the nearest star in the Orion constellation , being around 17.5 lightyears away from the Sun . The main sequence star is a red dwarf with the spectral class M3.5V.
Alpha Sextantis ( α Sex , α Sextantis ) is the brightest star in the constellation Sextans .
66 Arietis ( abbreviated 66 Ari ) is a double star in the northern constellation of Aries .
Phi Tauri ( φ Tau , φ Tauri ) is a binary star in the constellation Taurus .
Henize 2 - 10 is a dwarf galaxy located 34 million light years away in the constellation of Pyxis .
Omega Piscium ( Omega Psc , ω Piscium , ω Psc ) is a star approximately 106 light years away from Earth , in the constellation Pisces .
HD 10307 ( HR 483 A ) is a star similar to the Sun in mass , temperature and metal content , situated about 41 light - years from Earth in the constellation Andromeda .
9 Aquarii ( abbreviated 9 Aqr ) is a yellow giant with a spectral type G8III and an absolute magnitude of 7.38 in the constellation Aquarius .
Psi Ophiuchi ( ψ Oph ) is a star in the constellation Ophiuchus .
Gliese 777 c , often catalogued as Gliese 777 Ac or simply HD 190360 c , is an extrasolar planet approximately 52 light - years away in the constellation of Cygnus .
HD 16417 b ( also called λ2 Fornacis b ) is an extrasolar planet located approximately 84 light years away in the constellation of Fornax , orbiting the 6th magnitude G - type main sequence star HD 16417 .
21 Lyncis ( 21 Lyn ) is a star in the constellation Lynx .
APM 08279 + 5255 is a very distant , broad absorption line quasar located in the constellation Lynx .
52 Persei ( 52 Per ) is a binary star in the constellation Perseus .
2MASS 0939 - 2448 ( full designation is 2MASS J09393548 - 2448279 ) is a probable system of two nearby T - type brown dwarfs , located in constellation Antlia at 17.4 light - years from Earth .
HD 188753 is a hierarchical triple star system approximately 151 light - years away in the constellation of Cygnus , the Swan .
NGC 4526 is a lenticular galaxy in the Virgo constellation that is seen nearly edge - on .
The Engraved Hourglass Nebula ( also known as MyCn 18 ) is a young planetary nebula situated in the southern constellation Musca about 8,000 light - years away from Earth .
HD 122430 is an orange giant star about 440 light years away in the constellation of Hydra on the celestial sphere .
HD 133002 is the Henry Draper Catalogue designation for a star in the northern constellation of Ursa Minor .
R Canum Venaticorum is a Mira variable star in the constellation Canes Venatici .

NGC 6811 is an open cluster in the constellation of Cygnus , near the constellation of Lyra .
Koposov I is a low - luminosity globular cluster in the constellation Virgo in the halo of the Milky Way galaxy .
72 Pegasi ( 72 Peg ) is a star in the constellation Pegasus .
WASP-5b is an extrasolar planet orbiting the star WASP-5 located over 967 light - years away in the constellation Phoenix .
Messier 48 ( also known as M 48 or NGC 2548 ) is an open cluster in the Hydra constellation .
Dwingeloo 1 is a barred spiral galaxy about 10 million light - years away from the Earth , in the constellation Cassiopeia .
The Snowflake Cluster is a cluster in Monoceros and is included in NGC 2264 .
Iota Delphini ( ι Del , ι Delphini ) is a star in the constellation Delphinus .
Rho Gruis ( ρ Gru ) is a star in the constellation Grus .
Rho Geminorum ( ρ Gem ) is a star system that lies approximately 59 light - years away in the constellation of Gemini , about 5 arcminutes east of Castor .
3C 401 is a powerful radio galaxy located in the constellation Draco .
HD 80230 , also known as g Carinae ( g Car ) , is a star in the constellation Carina .

HD 200661 is a K - type star in the constellation Equuleus .
6 Equulei is an A - type main sequence star in the constellation of Equuleus with an apparent magnitude of 6.07 .
Gliese 22 , also catalogued V547 Cassiopeiae , is a hierarchical star system approximately 33 light - years away in the constellation of Cassiopeia .
HD 53143 is a star in the Carina constellation , located about 59.8 light - years ( 18.3 parsecs ) from the Earth .
Rho Coronae Borealis ( ρ CrB , ρ Coronae Borealis ) is a Solar twin , yellow dwarf star approximately 57 light - years away in the constellation of Corona Borealis .

Mario Schjetnan is a Mexican architect and landscape architect that manages to `` unite social concerns , aesthetics and , increasingly , ecology- all by way of interpreting and celebrating Mexico 's rich and diverse culture . ''

Super Roots 7 is the sixth installment in the Super Roots EP series by noise rock band Boredoms , released in 1998 by Warner Music Japan .
The Nanny is an American television sitcom originally aired on CBS from 1993 to 1999 , starring Fran Drescher as Fran Fine , a Jewish Queens native who becomes the nanny of three children from the New York / British high society .
Ashes and Snow by Canadian artist Gregory Colbert is an installation of photographic artworks , films , and a novel in letters that travels in the Nomadic Museum , a temporary structure built exclusively to house the exhibition .
Verbotene Liebe ( pronounced ( fɛɐ̯ˈboːtənə ˈliːbə ) , lit . `` Forbidden Love '' ) is a German television soap opera created by Reg Watson for Das Erste .
The Mass at Bolsena is a painting by the Italian renaissance artist Raphael .
Welcome Back , Kotter is an American sitcom starring Gabe Kaplan as a wisecracking , high school teacher in charge of a racially and ethnically diverse remedial class called the `` Sweathogs '' .
Created by Kevin Laffan , Emmerdale Farm was first broadcast on 16 October 1972 .
L'Absinthe ( English : The Absinthe Drinker or Glass of Absinthe ) is a painting by Edgar Degas .
Annika Bengtzon is a fictional character in a Scandinavian noir book and film series created by the Swedish journalist , publisher and crime writer Liza Marklund .
Flower of the Fields is an 1845 painting on wood by Lyon artist Louis Janmot .
The Railway , widely known as Gare Saint - Lazare , is an 1873 painting by Édouard Manet .
Happy Since I Met You is a television play written by Victoria Wood , and broadcast on ITV on 9 August 1981 .
The Siena Cathedral Pulpit is an octagonal structure in Siena Cathedral sculpted by Nicola Pisano and his assistants Arnolfo di Cambio , Lapo di Ricevuto , and Nicolas ' son Giovanni Pisano between the fall of 1265 and the fall of 1268 .
The Loves of Paris and Helen is a 1788 painting by Jacques - Louis David , showing Helen of Troy and Paris from Homer 's Iliad .
The Knitting Girl ( French : La Couseuse ) is a painting created by nineteenth century French artist William - Adolphe Bouguereau in 1869 .
In the dull village is an etching and aquatint print made by David Hockney in 1966 , one of series of illustrations for a selection of Greek poems written by Constantine P. Cavafy .
Standard Portable Intermediate Representation ( SPIR ) is an intermediate language for parallel compute and graphics by Khronos Group , originally developed for use with OpenCL .
Super Roots 3 is the third installment of the Super Roots EP series by Japanese experimental band Boredoms .
The Adventures of Blinky Bill is an Australian animated television series based on Dorothy Wall 's books about Blinky Bill .
The Santa Lucia de ' Magnoli Altarpiece ( Italian : Pala di Santa Lucia de ' Magnoli ) is a painting by the Italian painter Domenico Veneziano , dated to around 1445 - -1447 .
Flowering Orchards is a series of paintings which Dutch artist Vincent van Gogh executed in Arles , in southern France in the spring of 1888 .
The Poet Reclining ( Le Poète allongé ) is a painting by Marc Chagall , painted in oils in 1915 .
Feast in the House of Simon the Pharisee , also known as Christ in the Home of Simon the Pharisee , is a painting by Peter Paul Rubens .
The Gypsy Girl ( sometimes erroneously referred to as Malle Babbe ) is a painting by the Dutch Golden Age painter Frans Hals , painted in 1628 and now in the Louvre Museum .
The Caress of a Bird ( correctly La Caresse d'un oiseau ) is a 1967 sculpture by Joan Miró made at his studio in Palma de Mallorca .
The Stanford bunny is a computer graphics 3D test model developed by Greg Turk and Marc Levoy in 1994 at Stanford University .
August Blue is an oil - on - canvas painting by British artist Henry Scott Tuke .
Nonviolent Communication ( abbreviated NVC , also called Compassionate Communication or Collaborative Communication ) is a communication process developed by Marshall Rosenberg beginning in the 1960s .
Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains ( Chinese : 富春山居圖 ) is one of the few surviving works by the painter Huang Gongwang ( 1269 - -1354 ) and it is considered to be among his greatest works .
Niagara Falls , from the American Side is a painting by the American artist Frederic Edwin Church ( 1826 - -1900 ) .
Walking to the Sky is a public sculpture by Jonathan Borofsky .
The Quantum Cloud is a contemporary sculpture , designed by Antony Gormley , located next to the Millennium Dome in London .
Sœur Thérèse.com is a French televised legal drama that ran on TF1 from September 30 , 2002 , until May 16 , 2011 , and was created by Michel Blanc .

Created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster , Lex Luthor first appeared in Superman ( comic book ) # 4 ( March 1940 ) and has since endured as the archenemy of Superman .
The Flight of Europa is a bronze Art Deco sculpture created by American artist Paul Manship in 1925 .
Monumental Head is a 1960 bronze sculpture by Alberto Giacometti , installed at the Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden in Washington , D.C. , in the United States .
King Gustav III of Sweden and his Brothers is an oil painting by the Swedish portrait painter Alexander Roslin showing Gustav with his two brothers , Prince Frederick Adolf and Prince Charles , later Charles XIII of Sweden .
Don Camillo ( ˈdɔŋ kaˈmillo ) is a character created by the Italian writer and journalist Giovannino Guareschi , based on a Roman Catholic priest , World War II partisan and detainee of the concentration camps of Dachau and Mauthausen , Don Camillo Valota .
Hezar Dastan ( Persian : هزاردستان‎‎ , also Romanized as Hezār Dastān ) ( 1979 - 1987 ) is a highly popular TV series in Iran directed by Ali Hatami .
The Fantastic Four was the first superhero team created by writer - editor Stan Lee and artist / co - plotter Jack Kirby , who developed a collaborative approach to creating comics with this title that they would use from then on .
Naked Woman Climbing a Staircase ( originally in French Femme nue montant l'escalier ) is a drawing done with pencil and charcoal on card made by Joan Miró in 1937 .

Chewin ' the Fat was a Scottish comedy sketch show , starring Ford Kiernan , Greg Hemphill and Karen Dunbar .
Antoine Doinel is a fictional character created by French film director François Truffaut .
Feature integration theory is a theory of attention developed in 1980 by Anne Treisman and Garry Gelade that suggests that when perceiving a stimulus , features are `` registered early , automatically , and in parallel , while objects are identified separately '' and at a later stage in processing .
The Comte de Rochefort is a secondary fictional character in Alexandre Dumas ' d'Artagnan Romances .

He is the co - founder of COLSA Corporation , a business enterprise which provides engineering and support services to NASA , U.S. Army , U.S. Air Force , U.S. Navy , Defense Intelligence Agency , and the Missile Defense Agency .
Tre Jean - Marie ( born 13 April 1993 in Hackney , London ) , is a British songwriter and record producer .

Mitchell Kappenberg ( born 5 May 1986 ) is a Dutch professional footballer , who currently plays for Ter Leede in the Dutch Topklasse .
Renáta Tímea Tolvai ( born 24 March 1991 ) , known professionally as Reni Tolvai , is a Hungarian pop singer , who won the 5th season of the Hungarian singing competition show Megasztár in 2010 .
Natwar Thakkar ( born 1932 ) , popularly known as Natwar bhai , is a Gandhian social worker from India who works in the Indian state of Nagaland .
Anne Merriman , MBE , MCommH , FRCPI , FRCP ( born 1935 , Liverpool , England ) is a British doctor , known for her pioneering work and influential research into palliative care in developing countries in Africa .

Lambert Simnel ( ca . 1477 -- ca . 1525 ) was a pretender to the throne of England .
Sir Barry Close , 1st Baronet ( 3 December 1756 -- 12 April 1813 ) was an army general in the East India Company and a political officer .
Eli Putievsky ( born 1942 ) ( Hebrew : אלי פוטיבסקי‎ ) is a botanist , a distinguished Israeli scientist at the Volcani Institute of Agricultural Research ( ARO ) in the field of herbs , medicinal and aromatic plants , and the head of ARO during 1999 - 2007 .
Khaled Afarah ( Arabic : خالد عفارة‎ , born 21 January 1974 ) is a Yemeni football Defender and Club Al - Tilal .
Mohammed Buba Marwa ( born September 9 , 1953 ) is a retired Nigerian army officer who served as governor of Borno State , and then Lagos State during the military administrations of Generals Ibrahim Babangida and Sani Abacha .
Michael Zander , QC , FBA , ( born 16 November 1932 in Berlin ) is a British legal scholar .
Alan Peckolick ( born 1940 in Bronx , NY ) is an American graphic designer , artist , and photographer .

Arne Rolighed ( born 2 June 1947 ) is a Danish former politician and the current president of the Danish Cancer Society until July 2010 .
Ueli Kestenholz ( born 10 May 1975 ) is a Swiss snowboarder and Speedriding pioneer .

Daniel Fleeman ( born 3 October 1982 ) is an English racing cyclist who rode as a professional between 2007 and 2011 .
Antonis Vardis ( Greek : Αντώνης Βαρδής ; 7 August 1948 -- 2 September 2014 ) was a Greek composer and singer .
Ida Pruitt ( 1888 -- 1985 ) , bi - cultural social worker , author , speaker , interpreter and 20th century contributor to Sino - American understanding .
Monica Knudsen ( born 25 March 1975 ) is a Norwegian football coach and former player who is managing Toppserien club LSK Kvinner .
Dr. Noureddin Kianouri ( 1915 Nour , Teheran -- November 1999 from Kia'i dynasty of Tabaristan ) was an Iranian architect and political leader .

Edward Elwyn Jones ( born 27 April 1977 ) is a Welsh conductor and organist .
David de Vries ( born 1961 ) is an Australian film writer , director and producer and a comic book artist and writer .

Moshe Hecht ( born 1985 in Queens , New York ) is an American Hasidic singer - songwriter and rabbi , best known as the eponymous lead singer of the folk rock group Moshe Hecht Band .
Yuriko Kobayashi ( Japanese : 小林 祐梨子 ; born 12 December 1988 in Hyōgo ) is a Japanese middle- and long - distance runner who specializes in the 1500 metres and 5000 metres .

The Wog Wog River is a perennial river of the Towamba River catchment , located in the South Coast region of New South Wales , Australia .
The Okanogan River ( known as the Okanagan River in Canada ) is a tributary of the Columbia River , approximately 115 mi ( 185 km ) long , in southern British Columbia and north central Washington .
The Mistassini River is a river in central Quebec , Canada , draining into the north - western portion of Lac Saint - Jean .
The Hoosic River , also known as the Hoosac , the Hoosick ( primarily in New York ) and the Hoosuck ( mostly archaic ) , is a 76.3-mile - long ( 122.8 km ) tributary of the Hudson River in the northeastern United States .
The Little Muskingum River is a tributary of the Ohio River , approximately 65 mi ( 105 km ) long , in southeast Ohio in the United States .
Allia , a stream flowing into the Tiber , is 18 kilometres ( 11 mi ) from Rome and the site of the Battle of the Allia , where Romans were defeated by the Gauls under Brennus in 387 BC . ( Some date the battle in 364 or 390 . )
The Sèvre Niortaise is a river in western France , flowing into the Atlantic Ocean .
The Bloukrans River ( Grahamstown ) is a tributary of the Kowie River , and is situated near Grahamstown in the Eastern Cape province of South Africa .
The Vidourle ( Vidorle in occitan ) is a river in southern France , flowing into the Mediterranean Sea in Le Grau - du - Roi .
The Vedeggio is a river of the Swiss Canton Ticino which rises on the slopes of Monte Camoghè ( 2200 m ) between Bellinzona and Lugano , crosses the plain of Vedeggio ( which takes its name from the river ) , and enters Lake Lugano at Agno .
The Benedore River rises in the Benedore River Reference Area and flows generally south southeast , through the Seal Creek Reference Area , before reaching its mouth with Bass Strait within the Croajingolong National Park in the Shire of East Gippsland .
The Bulkley River in British Columbia is a major tributary of the Skeena River .
The Eastmain River is a river in northwestern Quebec which rises in north central Quebec and flows 800 km west to drain into James Bay .
The Kankakee River ( ( ˌkæŋkəˈki ) ) is a tributary of the Illinois River , approximately 133 miles ( 214 km ) long , in northwestern Indiana and northeastern Illinois in the United States .

Guno Berenstein ( born December 18 , 1967 in Nickerie , Suriname ) is a Dutch judoka who competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics in the men 's extra - lightweight division .

Rocío Ybarra Solaun ( born December 26 , 1984 in Bilbao , Vizcaya ) is a field hockey defender from Spain , who represented her native country at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Federico Gay ( 16 July 1896 -- 15 April 1989 ) was an Italian professional road bicycle racer , who won four stages in the 1924 Giro d'Italia , and one stage in the 1922 Tour de France .
Jiang Xishang ( born 15 May 1980 ) is a Chinese professional field hockey player who represented China at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing .
Jesper Tørring ( born 27 September 1947 ) is a Danish former athlete who competed in 110 metres hurdles and long jump at the 1972 Summer Olympics and in high jump at the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Henk Marcel Dost ( born September 28 , 1969 in Zierikzee , Zeeland ) is a retired decathlete from the Netherlands , who represented his native country at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , United States .
Nicolaas Tates ( born May 5 , 1915 -- December 25 , 1990 ) was a Dutch canoeist who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Crispin Duenas ( born January 5 , 1986 in North York , Ontario , grew up in Scarborough , Ontario ) is a Canadian recurve archer who represented Canada at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing and the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Lucy Morton ( 23 February 1898 -- 26 August 1980 ) , later known by her married name Lucy Heaton , was an English competition swimmer who represented Great Britain at the 1924 Summer Olympics and won a gold medal in the 200-metre breaststroke event .
Andrey Kislykh ( born 24 November 1976 ) is a Russian former hurdler who competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Félix Aznar is a Spanish skier who has served as para - alpine guide for Paralympic skiers including Andrés Boira and Gabriel Gorce , skiing with Gorce at the 2010 Winter Paralympics in Vancouver .
Brett Leaver ( born 12 January 1970 ) is a former field hockey player from New Zealand , who finished in eighth position with the Men 's National Team , nicknamed Black Sticks , at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .
Maryanne Graham ( born November 23 , 1955 ) , also known by her married name Maryanne Keever , is an American former competition swimmer who represented the United States at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Quebec .
Andrei Xepkin Xepkina ( Ukrainian : Андрій Щепкін , born 1 May 1965 in Zaporizhzhia , Ukraine ) is a Spanish and former Ukrainian handball player who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics for Spain .
Molly O'Bryan Vandemoer ( born 13 April 1979 ) is an American sailor who competed in the 2012 Summer Olympics in the Elliott 6 m class with Anna Tunnicliffe and Deborah Capozzi coming 5th overall .
Torsten Lennart Samuelsson ( 7 July 1924 -- 27 November 2012 ) was a Swedish association football player , who won bronze medals at the 1950 FIFA World Cup and 1952 Summer Olympics .
Kanako Kitao ( born 6 February 1982 ) is a Japanese synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Silvia Manrique Pérez ( born March 6 , 1973 in Llodio , Álava ) is a former field hockey player from Spain , who was a member of the Women 's National Team that won the gold medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics on home soil ( Barcelona ) .
Janine Beermann ( born 20 November 1983 in Wuppertal ) is a German field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Igor Vušurović ( born September 24 , 1974 ) is a Montenegrin volleyball player , who won the gold medal with the Yugoslavian Men 's National Team at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Luděk Bohman ( born 2 December 1946 in Nymburk ) is a Czech former athlete who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Jacques Brinkman ( born August 26 , 1966 in Utrecht ) is a former Dutch field hockey player , who twice won the golden medal with the national squad : at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta and four years later , at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney .
Philippe Tesnière was a professional cyclist between 1978 and 1981 , finishing in last place in the 1978 Tour de France .
On March 9 , 2006 Texas Lightning won the German heat for the Eurovision Song Contest 2006 and represented Germany in the Finals on May 20 , 2006 in Athens , Greece .
Karl Wahlmüller ( October 22 , 1913 in Linz -- February 16 , 1944 in Toila , Estonia ) was an Austrian football ( soccer ) player who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Shagun Chowdhary finished in 20th place in the trap shooting event at the 2012 Summer Olympics taking place in London .
Frank Forberger ( March 5 , 1943 -- September 30 , 1998 ) was a German rower who competed for East Germany in the 1968 Summer Olympics and in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Romário starred for Brazil in their 1994 FIFA World Cup triumph , receiving the FIFA Golden Ball as player of the tournament .
Otto Neumann ( 28 August 1902 -- 12 April 1990 ) was a German sprinter who competed at the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Ārons Bogoļubovs ( born December 30 , 1938 ) was a Latvian judoka who competed for the Soviet Union in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Lou Yun ( simplified Chinese : 楼云 ; traditional Chinese : 樓雲 ; pinyin : Lóu Yún ; born June 23 , 1964 in Hangzhou , Zhejiang ) is a retired Chinese gymnast who competed in the 1984 and 1988 Summer Olympics games , winning the vault twice .
Walter Frescura ( born 12 May 1940 ) is an Italian former sport shooter who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics , in the 1976 Summer Olympics , and in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Mercedes Coghen Alberdingk - Thijm ( born August 2 , 1962 in Madrid ) is a former field hockey player from Spain , who captained the Women 's National Team that won the golden medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics on home soil ( Barcelona ) .
Million Wolde ( Amharic : ሚሊዮን ወልዴ ; born March 17 , 1979 ) is an Ethiopian athlete , winner of the 5000 metres at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Andrés Aldama Cabrera ( born April 9 , 1956 ) is a retired amateur Cuban boxer , who won the light welterweight silver medal at the 1976 Summer Olympics and the Welterweight gold medal at the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Camillo Müller ( born January 2 , 1870 , date of death unknown ) was an Austrian sabre fencer who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics .

Edo Kovačević ( 16 November 1906 -- 15 March 1993 ) was a Croatian artist , best known for his colourful landscapes and views of suburban Zagreb .
Aniello Falcone ( 15 November 1600 -- 1656 ) was an Italian Baroque painter , active in Naples and noted for his painted depictions of battle scenes .
Caroline Decker Gladstein ( 1912 - -1992 ) was a labor activist in the 1930s in California , and an active organizer for the Cannery and Agricultural Workers '' International Union ( CAWIU ) .
Antenor Lucas , better known as Brandãozinho ( born in Campinas , Brazil , June 9 , 1925 -- died in São Paulo , Brazil , April 4 , 2000 ) was a Brazilian football defender .

Luigi Macchi ( 3 March 1832 in Viterbo - 29 March 1907 in Rome ) was an Italian Catholic nobleman and a Cardinal .
Eddie Baily died on 13 October 2010 at Welwyn Garden City after a short illness .
Beatrice Wood died nine days after her 105th birthday in Ojai , California .
A long - term professor of anatomy and physical anthropology , Hermann Klaatsch died unexpectedy in Eisenach in 1916 .
Stefan Bryła ( born 17 August 1886 in Kraków -- 3 December 1943 in Warsaw , Poland ) was a Polish construction engineer and welding pioneer .
Parri Spinelli ( ca . 1387 - 1453 ) was an Italian ( Tuscan ) painter of the early renaissance who was born in the Province of Arezzo .
Joan Perry died from emphysema in September 1996 at age 85 in Montecito , California .
Ruben Josefson , born 25 August 1907 in Svenljunga , Sweden , died 19 March 1972 in Uppsala , Sweden was a Swedish bishop within the Church of Sweden .
Albert Martin Bolton , Sr . , known as Al Bolton ( October 24 , 1925 -- April 2 , 2014 ) , was for forty - seven years a television or radio meteorologist from his adopted city of Shreveport , Louisiana .
Juan Joya Cordero ( February 25 , 1934 , Lima -- March 29 , 2007 ) was a Peruvian football ( soccer ) player , recognized as one of Peru 's most important strikers .
Enzo Rosa ( Balzola , April 24 , 1913 -- Varazze , February 20 , 1994 ) was an Italian professional football player .
Rudolf Reicke ( born 5 February 1825 , Memel , Germany -- d . 16 October 1905 , Königsberg , Germany ) was a German historian and scholar of Kant .
Johann Gottfried Tannauer , or Dannhauer ( 1680 , Saxony -1733/37 , Saint Petersburg ) was a German painter , portraitist and miniaturist who worked in Russia after 1711 .
Franz Seraph Stirnbrand ( c.1788/94 - 2 August 1882 , Stuttgart ) was a German portrait painter .
Maurice Gross ( born July 21 , 1934 in Sedan , Ardennes department ; died December 8 , 2001 in Paris ) was a French linguist and scholar of Romance languages .
Diego Carpitella ( Reggio di Calabria , 1924 - Rome , 1990 ) Italian professor of ethnomusicology at La Sapienza University in Rome .

Domenico Zipoli ( 17 October 1688 -- 2 January 1726 ) was an Italian Baroque composer who worked and died in Córdoba ( Argentina ) .
Agustín González Martínez , ( Madrid , 24 March 1930 - Madrid , 16 January 2005 ) was a Spanish actor .
Heinz Zemanek went to a secondary school in Vienna and earned his Matura in 1937 .
Georg Friedrich Sartorius ( after 1827 Freiherr von Waltershausen ; 25 August 1765 Kassel -- 24 August 1828 Göttingen ) was a German research historian , economist and professor at Göttingen University .
Pieter Nieuwland ( 5 November 1764 , Diemermeer -- 14 November 1794 , Leiden ) was a Dutch nautical scientist , chemist , mathematician , and poet .
Born in Montefalco , Aristide Rinaldini studied at the seminary of the Vatican ( 1860 - -1862 ) , Almo Collegio Capranica in Rome ( 1862 - -1868 ) , and the Pontifical Gregorian University , from where he obtained his doctorate in philosophy and licentiate in theology .
Sámuel Kálnoky became the first chancellor of Transylvania in Vienna and received the rank of count by the Habsburgs ( 1697 full title : count Kálnoky baron of Kőröspatak ) .
Émile Lévy ( August 29 , 1826 in Paris -- 1890 ) was a French genre and portrait painter .

John Charles Vivian ( June 30 , 1889 in Golden , CO , to February 10 , 1964 in Golden , CO ) was a United States attorney , journalist , and Republican politician who served as the 30th Governor of the State of Colorado from 1943 to 1947 .
Raul Renter ( 1 August 1920 , Tallinn -- 20 November 1992 , Tallinn ) was an Estonian economist and chess player , who twice won the Estonian Chess Championship .
Abdul Ghafoor Breshna ( Persian : عبدالغفود برشنا‎ ; born 10 April 1907 in Kabul ) was an Afghan painter , music composer , poet and film director .
Pier Francesco Foschi ( 1502 - -1567 ) was an Italian painter active in Florence in a Mannerist style .
Maria Koszutska ( pseudonym Wera Kostrzewa ) ( 2 February 1876 , Główczyn - 9 July 1939 , Moscow ) was a leader and theoretician of the Polish Socialist Party `` Left '' faction ( Polska Partia Socialistyczna , PPS -- Lewica ) and later of the Communist Party of Poland ( KPP ) .
Marie Jahoda ( 26 January 1907 , Vienna -- 28 April 2001 , Sussex ) was an Austrian - British social psychologist .
Oceana Wardlaw Martin Snead ( September 1885 -- November 29 , 1909 ) also known as Ocey Snead , was drugged and drowned in East Orange , New Jersey , by her own family to collect $ 32,000 ( equivalent to $ 840,000 in 2016 ) in insurance money .

Karl Mayreder ( 13 June 1856 in Mauer ( today a suburb of Vienna ) -- 9 September 1935 in Vienna ) was an Austrian architect .
Albert Bruce Jackson ( 14 February 1876 , in Newbury , Berkshire -- 14 January 1947 , in Kew ) was a British botanist and dendrologist .
Elizaphan Ntakirutimana ( 1924 , in Kibuye , Rwanda -- January 22 , 2007 in Arusha , Tanzania ) was a pastor of the Seventh - day Adventist Church in Rwanda and was the first clergyman to be convicted for a role in the 1994 Rwandan Genocide .
James V. Kern ( September 22 , 1909 , New York City , New York -- November 9 , 1966 , Encino , California ) was an American singer , songwriter , screenwriter , actor , and director .
John Neagle ( 4 November 1796 -- 17 September 1865 ) was a fashionable American painter , primarily of portraits , during the first half of the 19th century in Philadelphia .
Henri Cliquet - Pleyel was a French composer born on March 12 , 1894 in Paris , and died in that city on May 9 , 1963 .
John Hart Hunter died of Congestion of the Lungs on February 12 , 1872 , at City Hospital in Galveston , Texas .

György Faludy ( September 22 , 1910 , Budapest -- September 1 , 2006 , Budapest ) , sometimes anglicized as George Faludy , was a Hungarian - born poet , writer and translator .
