Norwegian biologist Kristine Bonnevie studied under Arnold Lang in Zürich in the years 1898 - 99 .
Angelo Italia ( 8 May 1628 -- 5 May 1700 ) was an Italian Jesuit and Baroque architect , who was born in Licata and died in Palermo .

George Noble Stearns ( September 29 , 1812 -- July 19 , 1882 ) was a tool designer and founded the George N. Stearns Company , a hardware business , in 1860 in Syracuse , New York .
Cornelius Galle ( bapt . 23 February 1615 , Antwerp -- 18 October 1678 , Antwerp ) , also called Cornelius Galle the Younger , was the grandson of Philip Galle and , like his father Cornelius Galle the Elder , and his grandfather , an engraver .

Giovanni Battista Lenardi ( active circa 1660 , died after 1703 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly in Rome .

Articulina is an extant suborder of Cyclostomatid bryozoan .
Terebra lanceata , common name the lance auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Pseudopulex is a genus of extinct , flea - like , parasitic insects that once fed on dinosaurs .
Cynoglossus canariensis , commonly known as the Canary tonguesole is a species of tonguefish .
Daphnia sinevi is a species of water flea from the Russian Far East .
Penicillium discolor is a species of the genus of Penicillium which occurs in nuts , vegetables and cheese and produces chaetoglobosins ( chaetoglobosin A - J ) , palitantin , cyclopenin , cyclopenol , cyclopeptin , dehydrocyclopeptin , viridicatin and viridicatol .
Mylochromis plagiotaenia is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is known from the southern arms of the lake .
Alcelaphus is a genus of antelope .
Prosartes trachycarpa , the roughfruit fairybells , rough - fruited fairybells or rough - fruited mandarin , is a North American species of plants in the lily family .
Stemmatodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Early Cretaceous epoch .
Kateretes is a genus of sap beetle .
Terminalia porphyrocarpa is a species of tree native to dry rainforests of Northeastern Australia and Papua New Guinea .
The single member ( species ) of this monotypic genus , Upolampes evena , is found in New Guinea , from West Irian to Papua New Guinea and Karkar Island ( Australasian ecozone ) .
Podocarpus parlatorei is a species of tree in the Podocarpaceae family and native to Argentina and Bolivia .
Makapania is an extinct genus of large caprid or ovibovine from the Pliocene and Pleistocene of southern and East Africa .
Enceliopsis argophylla , commonly known as the silverleaf sunray , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Digitaria insularis is a species of grass commonly known as sourgrass .
Amphimallon nigripenne is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that is endemic to Turkey .
Mertensia oblongifolia is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names oblongleaf bluebells and sagebrush bluebells .
Gibberrhynchium is a monotypical afrotropical genus of potter wasps .
Climacograptus was a Cambrian genus of graptolite .
Paraphaula porosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraphaula .
Somatochlora margarita , the Texas emerald , is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae .
Caesalpinia pulcherrima is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is native to the tropics and subtropics of the Americas .
Pseudogrammopsis lineata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudogrammopsis .
Atriplex elegans is a species of saltbush known by the common name wheelscale saltbush , Mecca orach , or wheelscale .
Campylotropsis is a plant genus consisting of a number of species of perennials native to Nepal , China , Korea and Taiwan .
Salvia longistyla , Mexican sage , is a Mexican plant species which flowers in mid - autumn .
Agave lechuguilla ( common name in Chihuahua : lechuguilla , meaning `` little lettuce '' ) is an agave species found only in the Chihuahuan Desert , where it is an indicator species .
Achondrostoma arcasii , termed the bermejuela , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Psammomys is a genus of rodents in the family Muridae .
Dinometa maputuana is a moth species in the family of Lasiocampidae found in Mozambique , South Africa and Tanzania .
Argyranthemum ( marguerite , marguerite daisy , dill daisy ) is a genus of flowering plants belonging to the family Asteraceae .
Chaenopsis coheni , the Cortez pikeblenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around the Isla Angel de la Guarda , in the Gulf of California , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Alloiococcus otitis is a species of bacteria first isolated from human middle - ear fluid , the type species of its genus .
Lateolabrax is a genus of commercially important fishes known as the Asian seabasses .
Ostracion is a genus of the boxfish family Ostraciidae .
Cyathea metteniana is a species of tree fern native to the Ryukyu Islands , Japan , and Taiwan , where it grows in wet forest , forest margins , and on hillsides .
Python europaeus is an extinct python species .
Tetraodon barbatus is a species of freshwater pufferfish found in the Mekong River .
Erethistidae are a family of catfishes that originate from southern Asia .
Staphyliniformia is a large infraorder of beetles .
Latrodectus karrooensis is a species of spider in the family Theridiidae , found in South Africa .
Taygetis thamyra , the Andromeda Satyr , is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Chiloglanis cameronensis is a species of upside - down catfish native to Cameroon , Equatorial Guinea and Gabon where they are found in the coastal rivers .
Prognathodes obliquus is a marine fish species of the butterflyfish family ( Chaetodontidae ) .
The Greenhouse Rove Beetle ( Dalotia coriaria ) is a species of staphylinid rove beetle in the subfamily Aleocharinae .
The Limnomedusae are an order of jellyfish in the class Hydrozoa .
Picea retroflexa ( Green dragon spruce ) is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family that is endemic to China , growing in West Sichuan , Kangding , Jiuzhaigou ( Zheduo Shan ) , Qinghai , and Ban Ma Xian .
Trichanthera is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the acanthus family containing the single species Trichanthera gigantea , which is known by many common names , including madre de agua , suiban , cenicero , tuno , naranjillo , and palo de agua .
Tipula paludosa is a species of true craneflies .
Vermilacinia nylanderi is classified in the subgenus Cylindricaria in which it is distinguished from related species by the thallus divided into numerous narrow tubular rugose branches , by the abundant fertile pycnidia , and by lichen substances of zeorin and ( -)-16-hydroxykaurane , occasionally with unknowns .
Sphictostethus nitidus , the golden hunter wasp or red spider wasp , is a species of pepsid spider wasp which is endemic to New Zealand .
Cantua pyrifolia is a species of flowering plant in the family Polemoniaceae in the order Ericales and is an endemic to Peru .
Phacelia leonis is a rare species of phacelia known by the common name Siskiyou phacelia .
Pectocarya heterocarpa is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names chuckwalla combseed and mixed - nut pectocarya .
The Oxalidales is an order of flowering plants , included within the rosid subgroup of eudicots .
Oeceoclades furcata is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to northwestern Madagascar , where it grows in sandy soils .
Epilobium montanum or Broad - leaved Willowherb is a species of willowherb .
It contains only one species , Vansomerenia rogersi or Rogers '' Gem , which is found in central Kenya and northern Tanzania .
Doronicum corsicum is a species of the genus Doronicum and the family sunflower family .
Lactobacillus fructivorans is one of the few species that successfully survives alcoholic fermentation and actually continues to grow and engage in cell multiplication afterwards .
Astragalus hypoxylus is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Huachuca milkvetch , or Huachuca Mountain milkvetch .
Mangifera siamensis ( also called Thai Mango , or Siamese Mango ) is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Phryssonotus is a genus of bristle millipedes containing around nine species .
Cistecephaloides is an extinct genus of dicynodont therapsid .
The Carolina madtom ( Noturus furiosus ) is a species of fish in the Ictaluridae family .
Salarias is a genus of combtooth blennies found in the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Spinaristobia rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinaristobia .
Acanthomysis microps is a species of mysid that was discovered during a study of the coastal waters of Maharashtra and South Gujarat that took place during 2008 and 2009 .
Orthonevra chilensis is a species of hoverfly first found in Chile .
Charaxes fournierae fournierae ( Cameroon , Gabon , Congo , Central African Republic , western Democratic Republic of Congo ) Charaxes fournierae jolybouyeri Vingerhoedt , 1998 ( Guinea , Ivory Coast , Ghana ) considered a full species by Vingerhoedt et al .
Eriogonum alpinum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Trinity buckwheat .
Matoatoa brevipes is a species of gecko found along the southwestern coast of Madagascar .
Leptomesosella uniformis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Leptomesosella .
Haliotis pourtalesii , common name Pourtale 's abalone , is a rare species of deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Lethrinus mahsena , common names the sky emperor , mahsena emperor , and cutthroat emperor , is a species of emperor fish .
Iredaleoconcha caporaphe is a species of air - breathing land snails or semislugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicarionidae .
Daviesia cordata , also known as Bookleaf , is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae .
Golden grey mullet is a pelagic species , usually inshore , entering lagoons , ports and estuaries , but rarely moves into freshwater .
Pomaulax gibberosus , common name the red turban , is a species of medium - sized to large sea snail with a calcareous operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Stychoides strandiellus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Stychoides .
Cereus elegans is a cactus species in the genus Cereus .
Chiromantis simus ( common names : Assam Asian frog , Assam tree frog , Annandale 's tree frog , Annandale 's pigmy tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in Bangladesh and northeastern India ( in Assam , Mizoram , and West Bengal states ) .
Hylopetes is a genus of flying squirrels .
Embiotoca lateralis , commonly known as the striped surfperch or striped seaperch , is a species of surfperch native to the North Eastern Pacific Ocean .
Sphagnum russowii , Russow 's sphagnum or Russow 's bogmoss , is a species of peat moss with a Holarctic distribution .
Heterodera elachista ( Japanese cyst nematode , Rice cyst nematode ) is a plant pathogenic nematode , which is cited as an invasive species .
Clathrina fjordica is a species of calcareous sponge of the genus Clathrina from Chile .
Jurassipanorpa is a genus of fossil scorpionfly ( order Mecoptera ) containing two species described in 2014 from the Jiulongshan Formation of Inner Mongolia , China .
Melanoides nyassana is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Thiaridae .
Tachina alacer is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to France .
Prunus brigantina , called Briançon apricot , marmot plum , and alpine apricot , is a wild tree species native to France and Italy .
Iguanura is a monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family from Southeast Asia , commonly called pinang .
Colobodactylus ( common name : Amaral 's teiids ) is a small genus of lizards that are endemic to Brazil .
Anabarilius transmontanus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus , that can be found in China and Vietnam .
Pelobates syriacus , the eastern spadefoot or Syrian spadefoot , is a species of toad in the family Pelobatidae , native to an area extending from Eastern Europe to Western Asia .
Phyllostegia hispida , the hispid phyllostegia , is an endangered species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae .
Dischistodus prosopotaenia is a species of damselfish known by the common names honey - head damsel and honey - breast damsel .
Atractaspis boulengeri , or the Central African burrowing asp , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Neopoeciloderma lepturoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Neopoeciloderma .
Yavnella argamani is a species of ant belonging to the Yavnella ant genus .
Allium curtum is a Middle Eastern species of onion in the amaryllis family .
Crossoloricaria is a genus of armored catfish native to South America with one species ranging into Central America .
Veitchia subdisticha is a plant species in the palm family .
Parahiekeia hebridarum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parahiekeia .
Aegista diversifamilia is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk from Taiwan .
Beauveria bassiana is a fungus that grows naturally in soils throughout the world and acts as a parasite on various arthropod species , causing white muscardine disease ; it thus belongs to the entomopathogenic fungi .
Remingtonocetidae is a diverse family of early aquatic mammals of the order Cetacea , endemic to the coastline of the ancient Tethys Ocean during the Eocene ( present - day Pakistan and India ) .
Knightia excelsa , commonly called rewarewa ( from Māori ) , is an evergreen tree endemic to the low elevation and valley forests of New Zealand 's North Island and Marlborough Sounds ( 41 ° S ) and the type species for the genus Knightia .
Tabellaria is a genus of diatoms ( Bacillariophyceae ) .
Astragalus tuyehensis is a plant species native to Iran .
Ledebouria revoluta , the South Indian squill , is a flowering plant species in the genus Ledebouria found in Southern Africa and India .
Prognatholiparis ptychomandibularis , the Wrinkle - jaw snailfish , is a species of snailfish native to the northeastern Pacific Ocean from near Seguam Island in the Aleutian Islands .
Daphnia commutata is a species of water flea .
Echinolittorina ziczac , previously known as Littorina ziczac , common name the `` zebra periwinkle '' , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Littorinidae .
Ambassis jacksoniensis , commonly known as the Port Jackson glassfish or Port Jackson perchlet , is a species of fish in the family Ambassidae native to eastern Australia .
Fernseea bocainensis is a species in the genus Fernseea .
Chlorella is a genus of single - cell green algae belonging to the phylum Chlorophyta .
Kerremansella rufitarsis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Kerremansella .
Quadrasiella clathrata is a species of minute , salt marsh snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks , or micromollusks , in the family Assimineidae .
Eudesmia is a genus of lichen moths in the Erebidae family .
Auplopus is a large genus of spider wasps belonging to the subfamily Pepsinae of the spider wasp family Pompilidae , distributed throughout the world except for Antarctica .
Sphallenopsis pilosovittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Sphallenopsis .
Lotus salsuginosus is a species of legume known by the common name coastal bird's - foot trefoil .
Trachyscorpia is a genus of rockfishes found in the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific oceans .
Melaleuca pallescens was first formally described in 1984 by Norman Byrnes in Austrobaileya as a new species .
Agriphila geniculea , also known as Elbow - striped Grass - veneer , is a species of moth of the family Crambidae .
Euzophera magnolialis , the magnolia root borer , is a species of snout moth in the genus Euzophera .
Semomesia is a genus of metalmark butterflies .
Polytmus is a small genus of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Haworthia is a large genus of small succulent plants endemic to Southern Africa ( Mozambique , Namibia , Lesotho , Swaziland , South Africa ) .
Pseudophilautus alto ( common name : Horton Plains shrub frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Talitrus is a genus of amphipod crustaceans , including the familiar European sandhopper Talitrus saltator .
It contains the single species Pyramidula tetragona distributed in central North America as well as Europe and Africa .
Paraschoenionta shelfordi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraschoenionta .
Mallosia imperatrix is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Iran , Lebanon , Syria , and Turkey .
Stathmonotus culebrai , the Panamanian worm blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in rocky reefs around Costa Rica and Panama , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Aeruginospora furfuracea is a species of fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae .
Senecio triangularis , known as arrowleaf ragwort , arrowleaf groundsel and arrowleaf butterweed , is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae .
Rubus glaucus , commonly known as Mora de Castilla or Andean Raspberry , is a species of blackberry found in Latin America from Oaxaca to Bolivia , including the northern and central Andes .

Cattleya lobata , commonly known as the Lobed Sophronitis , is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Minas Gerais ) .
Melica glabrescens is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Buenos Aires and Río Negro provinces of Argentina .
Euconocephalus remotus is a species of insect in the family Tettigoniidae .
Sinocorophium hangangense is a species of gammaridean amphipod found mainly in Korea .
Pseudognaphalium canescens ( syn . Gnaphalium canescens ) is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Wright 's cudweed .
Hyastenus bispinosus is a species of crab in the family Epialtidae , found around Ambon , the Banda Islands , Timor and the Lembeh Strait off Sulawesi .
Pogonoscorpius sechellensis is a species of scorpionfish native to the Indian Ocean from the vicinity of the Seychelles where it has been found at depths down to 68 metres ( 223 ft ) .
Desmocerataceae is a superfamily of Cretaceous ammonites , generally with round or oval - whorled shells that are mostly smooth or weakly ribbed and rarely tuberculate , but commonly with constrictions .
Eragrostis superba is a species of perennial tufted grass in the Poaceae family .
Prosartes hookeri is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family known by the common names drops of gold and Hooker 's fairy bells .
The Onagraceae are a family , known as the willowherb family or evening primrose family , of flowering plants .
Hyposmocoma humerovittella is a species of moth of the family Cosmopterigidae .
Pycnoporidium is thought to be a genus of red or green alga ; one species has been synonymized with the brachiopod Gosaukammerella , leaving the interpretation of the other species uncertain .
Heterogyrus milloti is a species of beetle in the family Gyrinidae , the only species in the genus Heterogyrus .

Metschnikowia is a genus of yeast in the family Metschnikowiaceae .

Parascorpaena mossambica , the Mozambique scorpionfish , is a species of Scorpionfish native to the Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean to Micronesia .

The species is named in honor of Ms. Jane Waldron , great - grandmother of Jessie Hill of Philadelphia and Hawaii , in recognition of Jessie Hill 's contribution to saving and inventorying the conserved ACG rain forest in which Dunama janewaldronae breeds .

Johngarthia lagostoma is a species of terrestrial crab that lives on Ascension Island and three other islands in the South Atlantic .

Caridina nilotica is a species of freshwater shrimp in the Atyidae family .
The family Huperziaceae is one of two families sometimes recognized in the order Lycopodiales , and contains two or three extant genera :
Woodnymphs are hummingbirds in the genus Thalurania .
Acytolepis is a genus of small butterflies that belongs to the Lycaenids or Blues family .
Paeonia mairei is a species of peony rare in cultivation .
Novopsocus magnus is a species of Pseudocaeciliidae that lives on the island of New Guinea .
Hyalinobatrachium is a genus of glass frogs characterized by having a bulbous liver covered by white pigment , a transparent parietal peritoneum , extensive membrane between the outer fingers , and lacking a humeral spine in adult males .
Micrelaps boettgeri , commonly known as Boettger 's two - headed snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Rhytisma fulvum , the sulphur leather coral , is a species of colonial soft coral in the family Alcyoniidae .
Pospiviroid is a genus of viroid which most commonly infects tubers .
Cedarpelta is an extinct genus of herbivorous basal ankylosaurid ankylosaur , based on material recovered from the Lower Cretaceous of North America .
Haplochromis aeneocolor is a species of cichlid endemic to Uganda where it is found in Lake George and the Kazinga Channel .
Gonium is a genus of colonial algae , a member of the order Volvocales .
Phlegra fasciata is a species of jumping spiders that can be found in Palearctic region .
Lebrunia coralligens , the hidden anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Aliciidae .
Xenotilapia burtoni is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from areas with sandy substrates in Burton Bay .
Pascua caudilinea , the Pascua goby , is a species of goby endemic to the waters around Easter Island .
Gleichenia alpina , commonly known as Alpine Coral - fern , is a small fern species that occurs in Tasmania and New Zealand .
Rhinodoras gallagheri is a species of thorny catfish known from Apure River , Capanaparo River , and Arauca River , all left bank tributaries of the middle Orinoco , in the llanos regions of Apure and Barinas States of Venezuela .
Bathyclarias worthingtoni is a species of airbreathing catfish endemic to Lake Malawi , in the countries of Malawi , Mozambique and Tanzania .
Murunducaris juneae is a species of crustacean in the family Parastenocarididae .
The black spotted bleak ( Alburnus caeruleus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the carp family , Cyprinidae .
Olivella nivea , the snowy dwarf olive , is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olivellidae , the dwarf olives .
Psilocybe aquamarina is a species of mushroom in the family Hymenogastraceae .
Phalloceros is a genus of poeciliids native to freshwater habitats in Brazil , Paraguay , Uruguay and northern Argentina .
Ischnochiton circumvallatus is a species of chiton in the family Ischnochitonidae .
Epidendrum frutex is a high - altitude species of reed - stemmed Epidendrum orchid native to Colombia , Ecuador , Peru , and Venezuela .
Anobium is a genus of beetles in the family Anobiidae .
Ametacyna holzschuhi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ametacyna .
Capensibufo is a small genus of true toads with only two species .
Suillus granulatus was first described by Carolus Linnaeus in 1753 as a species of Boletus .
Lanthanosuchoidea is an extinct superfamily of ankyramorph parareptiles from the late Cisuralian to the middle Guadalupian epochs ( Artinskian - Wordian stages ) of Europe , North America and Asia .
Deconica neorhombispora is a species of agaric fungus in the family Strophariaceae .
Solaster spectabilis is an extant species of starfish described in 2011 , and indigenous to the waters surrounding the Aleutian Islands in the North Pacific Ocean .
Actinopyga is a genus of sea cucumbers found in coastal waters in tropical and temperate regions .
Abbottina liaoningensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Abbottina found in the Liaoning Province of China .
Plasmaviridae is a family of bacteria - infecting viruses .
Antennaria arcuata ( box pussytoes ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Tephrocactus ( from Greek tephra , `` ash '' , referring to the color of these plants ' epidermis ) is a genus of the cactus family ( Cactaceae ) .
Ischnura erratica , the swift forktail , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Plagiopsetta is a genus of crested flounders native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Smidtia conspersa is a species of tachinid fly .
Sisyrinchium septentrionale , the northern blue - eyed grass , is a plant species native to western Canada ( British Columbia , Alberta , Saskatchewan , and Northwest Territories ) .
Cupressus guadalupensis , the Guadalupe cypress , is a species of cypress from Guadalupe Island in the Pacific Ocean off western North America .
Serixiophytoecia vitticollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Serixiophytoecia .
Uncinia uncinata ( also known as Hawai'i birdcatching sedge ' , hook sedge , bastard grass , kamu or matau - a - maui ) is a species of plant in the Cyperaceae family .
Bombus polaris is a common Arctic bumblebee species .
Xeromphalina setulipes is a species of fungus of the family Mycenaceae .
Xanthosoma brasiliense is a species of flowering plant in the Araceae .
The Djibouti francolin ( Pternistis ochropectus ) is one of over forty species of francolins , a group of birds in the Phasianidae family .
Aeger tipularius is a species of fossil prawn from the Solnhofen Plattenkalk .
Beggiatoa is a genus of bacteria in the order Thiotrichales .
Rhynchocypris percnurus , known alternatively as the lake minnow or the swamp minnow , is a Eurasian species of small freshwater cyprinid fish .
Pethia khugae is a species of cyprinid fish native to India where it is found in the Chindwin River basin , occurring in clear , relatively fast - flowing streams .
Anochetus longifossatus , is a species of ant of the subfamily Ponerinae , which can be found from Sri Lanka .
Siats is an extinct genus of large megaraptoran theropod dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous Cedar Mountain Formation of Utah , US .
Circaeasteraceae is a family of two species of herbaceous plants native to China and the Himalayas .
Samydaceae is a family of tropical and subtropical woody plants , its best known genus being Casearia .
Chthonophis ( meaning `` snake beneath the earth '' , from the Greek chthonios ( `` beneath the earth '' ) and ophis ( `` snake '' ) ) is an extinct genus of amphisbaenian lizard with only one known species , Chthonophis subterraneus , from the earliest Paleocene of northeastern Montana .
Octopus sasakii is a species of octopus found only in salt water .
The spider genus Pholcus contains the cellar spider P. phalangioides , often called the `` daddy longlegs '' .
Fissurella microtrema , common name the rugose slit limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Cucumis myriocarpus ( paddy melon ) is often confused with Citrullus lanatus ( the Afghan or camel melon ) in Australia , where both species are introduced .
Tipuloidea is a superfamily of flies containing the living families Pediciidae and Tipulidae and the extinct families Architipulidae and Eolimnobiidae .
Argenteohyla siemersi ( common name : red - spotted Argentina frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Phaius tancarvilleae is a species of orchid widespread in the Indian Subcontinent , New Guinea , China , Japan , Southeast Asia , Indonesia , Malaysia , the Philippines , Australia and certain islands of the Pacific .
Athyris is a brachiopod genus with a subequally biconvex shell that is generally wider than long and a range that extends from the Silurian into the Triassic .
Pagurus sinuatus is a large species of hermit crab found in Australia and the Kermadec Islands .
Lilium parvum is a species of lily known by the common names Sierra tiger lily and alpine lily .
Ajania is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , described as a genus in 1955 .
Myxodagnus opercularis , the Dart stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the coastal waters of Baja California Sur , Mexico where it can be found on sandy bottoms .
The Pallid spiny softshell turtle ( Apalone spinifera pallida ) is a subspecies of softshell turtle native to the United States , in the states of Oklahoma , Louisiana and Texas .
Pyrgomantis fasciata is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Tanzania , Mozambique , Transvaal and the Congo River region .
Ternstroemia luquillensis , the palo colorado , is a species of plant in the Pentaphylacaceae family .
Syncope bassleri ( common name : Bassler 's humming frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Euprenolepis procera is a species of ant found in the rainforests of South East Asia .
Telmatobius atahualpai ( common name : Amazonas water frog ) is a species of frog in the Telmatobiidae family .
Tapinella panuoides is a fungus species in the genus Tapinella .
Smilax illinoensis , the Illinois greenbrier , is a North American species of plants found only in the United States and Canada .
Sobralia macrantha , commonly known as the large - flowered sobralia , is a species of orchid found from north - central and southern Mexico to Central America .
Nigella is a genus of about 14 species of annual plants in the family Ranunculaceae , native to southern Europe , north Africa , south and southwest Asia .
Pelophila is a genus of beetles in the ground beetle family , containing the following species :
Litopenaeus is a genus of prawns , formerly included in the genus Penaeus .
Cladonia macrophyllodes , commonly known as the large - leaved cladonia , is a species of lichen in the genus Cladonia .
Vancleavea is a genus of extinct , armoured , non - archosaurian archosauriform with relatively small limbs from the Late Triassic of western North America .
Nemateleotris magnifica , the Fire Goby , Fire Fish , Fire Dartfish , or Red Fire Goby is a species of dartfish native to the Indian and Pacific oceans from the eastern coast of Africa to the Hawaiian Islands and from the Austral Islands north to the Ryukyu Islands .
Dactylanthus antarcticus is a species of sea anemones in the order Actiniaria .
The only species it contains is Lapidaria margaretae , also known as the Karoo rose .
Cycas changjiangensis is a plant species in the cycad order , Cycadales .
Zamia acuminata is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family which is threatened by habitat loss .
Lespedeza cuneata is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Chinese bushclover and sericea lespedeza , or just sericea .
Erythronium pluriflorum is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family which is known by the common names manyflower fawn lily , golden fawn - lily , and Shuteye Peak fawn lily .
Callionymus semeiophor is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific Ocean around Indonesia .
Qianlabeo striatus is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Pearl River drainage , Guizhou , China .
Tessarecphora arachnoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tessarecphora .
Anomaloglossus stepheni ( common name : Stephen 's rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Zodarion pusio is a spider species found in Bosnia - Hercegovina , Croatia , France , Italy and Tunisia .
Eucalyptus spathulata , commonly known as Swamp Mallet , is a species of Eucalyptus which is endemic to Western Australia .
Siphonariidae is a taxonomic family of small to medium - sized air - breathing sea snails , marine and brackish water pulmonate gastropod molluscs .
Dorcaschesis sericata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dorcaschesis .
Pseudohemiodon amazonus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the lower Amazon basin .
Mimohyllisia tonkinensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimohyllisia .
Patiriella gunnii is an Australian species of sea star . It has six arms and can be any colour .
Wapuskanectes is an extinct genus of elasmosaurid known from the Alberta of Canada .
Philanthus gibbosus , which is commonly referred to as a beewolf due to its predation practices , is a species of bee - hunting wasp and is the most common and widespread member of the genus in North America .
Otothyris travassosi is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the coastal streams of the southeast .
Carangidae is a family of fish which includes the jacks , pompanos , jack mackerels , runners , and scads .
Hemiphractus fasciatus , or the banded horned treefrog , is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Arabis macdonaldiana is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name MacDonald 's rockcress .
Boromys is an extinct genus of Cuban rodents in the family Echimyidae .
Hypocassida subferruginea is a species of leaf beetle belonging to the family Chrysomelidae .
Xanthosia rotundifolia is a species of the plant family Mackinlayaceae , but sometimes also placed in Araliaceae or Apiaceae .
Didymoceras navarroensis is an extinct heteromorph ammonite species from the upper Campanian to lower Maastrichtian ( 83.5 to 66 million years ago ) .
Xyris serotina , the acidswamp yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plants in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Phylladiorhynchus is a genus of squat lobsters in the family Galatheidae , containing the following species :
Pennantia baylisiana is a species of plant in the Pennantiaceae family ( Icacinaceae in older classifications ) .
Caulanthus crassicaulis is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name thickstem wild cabbage .
Solidago leiocarpa , common name Cutler 's alpine goldenrod , or ( in Québec ) verge d’or de Cutler , is a plant species native to mountainous portions of Québec , northern New England , and northern New York State .
Proceratiinae is a subfamily of ants in the poneromorph subfamilies group , with three extant genera , of which most are tropical or subtropical , although overall distribution is worldwide .
Turbonilla nereia is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod micromollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
No fossils can be confidently assigned to the Chirostyloidea , although Pristinaspina may belong either in the family Kiwaidae or Chirostylidae .
Tetrapathaea tetrandra is a plant species endemic to New Zealand , the only species of the genus Terapathaea currently recognized .
Chionachne is a genus of Asian , Australian , and Papuasian plants in the grass family .
Bebearia is a genus of brush - footed butterflies .
Lupinus microcarpus , the wide - bannered lupine or chick lupine , is a species of lupine native to western North America from southwestern British Columbia south through Oregon and California , including the Mojave Desert , and into Baja California .
Trochosa robusta is a cellar spider species with Palearctic distribution .
Solanum lasiocarpum is of interest to botanists because of its strong resemblance to , and apparent close relation to South American species , the cocona ( S. sessiliflorum ) , the naranjilla ( S. quitoense ) , and the pseudolulo ( S. pseudolulo ) in particular .
Guayuriba dilaticeps is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Guayuriba .
Orthopichonia is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae family , first described as a genus in 1953 .
Farlowella taphorni is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Torondoy River basin in the Lake Maracaibo drainage .
Loeseliastrum schottii is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Schott 's calico .
Helops rossii is a species of darkling beetles belonging to the family Tenebrionidae subfamily Tenebrioninae .
Opilia is a genus of approximately 33 species of lianas in the family Opiliaceae described as a genus in 1802 .
The Atheriniformes , also known as the silversides , are an order of ray - finned fishes that includes the Old World silversides and several less - familiar families , including the unusual Phallostethidae .
Willughbeia is a genus of plant in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1820 .
Hemitaurichthys is a genus of butterflyfishes native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .
The Trigoides genus is known from fossils from the Chengjiang Lagerstätte .
Batasio tigrinus is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the genus Batasio in the family Bagridae , known from Thailand .
Orthetrum sabina , the Slender Skimmer or Green Marsh Hawk , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Laomenes cornutus is a species of saltwater shrimp found in the Maldives that was first described in 1915 .
Lactococcus is a genus of lactic acid bacteria that were formerly included in the genus Streptococcus Group N1 .
Megatypus is an extinct genus of insect of the order Meganisoptera .
Cretornis is a pterosaur genus containing the single species Cretornis hlavaci .
Lunostoma is an extinct genus of bryozoans which existed during the middle Devonian of what is now Germany , precisely from the Gerolstein syncline .
Spodiopogon is a genus of Asian plants in the grass family .
Sida javensis , common name in Taiwan translating as `` Java golden flower noon '' is a plant species apparently native to Indonesia , Malaysia , the Philippines and Taiwan , but naturalized in the West Indies and parts of Africa .
Cerithiidae , common name the cerithiids or ceriths , is a large family of medium - sized marine gastropods in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Habenaria dentata is a species of orchid native to the Himalaya , China , India , Indochina , Thailand and Myanmar .
Nebria aenea is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Kazakhstan and Russia .
Helvella leucomelaena , commonly known as the `` white - footed elf cup '' , is a species of fungi in the Helvellaceae family , Pezizales order .
Milnesium berladnicorum is a species of Eutardigrade in the family Milnesiidae , native to Bârlad , Romania .
Cartonema is a genus of perennial or annual monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family .
Leptolalax kajangensis ( Kajang slender litter frog ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Isbrueckerichthys calvus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Tibagi River basin .
Branchinecta paludosa is a species of fairy shrimp with a Holarctic distribution .
Sebastidae is a family of marine fish in the order Scorpaeniformes .
Nemadoras is a genus of thorny catfishes native to tropical South America .
Sagittaria kurziana , common names springtape and strap - leaf sagittaria , is an aquatic plant species native to Florida and naturalized in the Mariana Islands .
Heterodraba is a monotypic genus of plants in the mustard family containing the single species Heterodraba unilateralis , which is known by the common name ladiestongue mustard .
Megalopta genalis is a species of the family Halictidae , otherwise known as the sweat bees .
Cycnoches ventricosum is a species of orchid native to southern Mexico and Central America .
Burgessia is an extinct genus of arthropod from the Middle Cambrian .
Goodeinae is a subfamily of splitfins .
Sankowskya stipularis is a genus and a sole known species of trees found only ( endemic ) in one locality in the Wet Tropics rainforests of north eastern Queensland , Australia .
Olearia floribunda , commonly known as Heath Daisy - bush , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae .
Pinus lawsonii , Lawson 's pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Cyclodendron is a genus of lycophyta and dating from the Permian .
Panamericansaurus is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now South America .
Squalius lucumonis , or brook chub is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Allosauroidea is a superfamily or clade of theropod dinosaurs which contains four families -- the Metriacanthosauridae , Allosauridae , Carcharodontosauridae , and Neovenatoridae .
Ithycyphus is a genus of venomous lamprophiid snakes found only on the island of Madagascar .
Parrella is a genus of gobies native to the tropical waters of the Pacific and Atlantic coasts of the Americas .
Capoeta caelestis , the Taurus scraper , is a species of freshwater cyprinid fish endemic to southern Anatolia , Turkey .
Holothuria thomasi , the tiger 's tail , is a species of sea cucumber in the family Holothuriidae .
Correlophus is a genus of lizards in the family Diplodactylidae endemic to New Caledonia .
Bryconamericus is a genus of characins found in Central and South America .
The Rapa fruit dove ( Ptilinopus huttoni ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Halidayopsis formosensis is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Halidayopsis of the family Tachinidae .
Euphorbia leuconeura , the Madagascar jewel , is a species of plant in the Euphorbiaceae family .
Ingolfiella longipes is a species of amphipod crustacean in the family Ingolfiellidae .
Chilantaisaurus ( `` Ch'i - lan - t'ai lizard '' ) is a genus of neovenatorid theropod dinosaur from the late Cretaceous Ulansuhai Formation of China ( Turonian stage , about 92 million years ago ) .
Petrochromis famula is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where they prefer rocky substrates that they can graze from .
Temnothorax pilagens ( from Latin : pilare , `` to pluck '' , `` plunder '' , `` pillage '' ) is a small Nearctic species of slave - making ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Trimetopon is a genus of colubrid snakes , which are endemic to Costa Rica .
Leptolalax sungi ( Sung toad or Sang 's metacarpal - tubercled toad ) is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Oleispira antarctica is a hydrocarbonoclastic marine bacterium , the type species in its genus .
Epilobium pygmaeum is a species of willowherb known by the common names pygmy willowherb , smooth spike - primrose and smooth boisduvalia .
Epipactis tremolsii is a species of terrestrial orchid of the genus Epipactis , belonging to the family Orchidaceae .
Pseudolabrus is a genus of wrasses native to the eastern Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean .
Trifolium incarnatum , known as crimson clover or Italian clover , is a species of clover in the family Fabaceae , native to most of Europe .
Orobates is an extinct genus of diadectid .
Pseudophoridae is an extinct family of tropical warm - water Paleozoic sea snails .
The Angelfish Orchid or Inward - bent Dendrobium ( Dendrobium aduncum ) is a species of orchid .
Rodriguezia sticta is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Espírito Santo , Minas Gerais , Rio de Janeiro ) .
Apate terebrans , common names shot - hole borer or trunk borer or girdler , is a species of horned powder - post beetles belonging to the family Bostrichidae .
Pisa armata is a species of crab from the eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Dendrochirus zebra , known commonly as the Zebra turkeyfish or Zebra lionfish among other vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Scorpaenidae .
Stagmomantis is a genus consisting of 27 species of mantises native to the Americas .
Phalaris angusta is a species of grass known by the common names timothy canarygrass and narrow canarygrass .
Microgastrinae is a subfamily of braconid wasps , encompassing 2,000 described species , with an estimated 5,000 - 10,000 total species .
Archaeogeryon peruvianus is an extinct species of crab from the Miocene , the only species in the genus Archaeogeryon .
Litocladius is a genus of chironomid midges that belongs to the subfamily Orthocladiinae and is composed of three species , Litocladius confusus Mendes et Andersen ( 2008 ) , Litocladius mateusi Mendes , Andersen & Sæther ( 2004 ) , and Litocladius floripa Mendes et Andersen ( 2008 ) all described from Brazil only .
Medinilla magnifica , showy medinilla , is a species in the genus Medinilla native to the Philippines .
Dipterocarpus cornutus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae endemic to peninsular Malaysia , Singapore , Sumatra and Kalimantan .
Cteniloricaria is a genus of armored catfishes native to northern South America .
Elaphe carinata , the king ratsnake ( also known as Taiwan stink snake ) , is a species of Colubrid snake found in Southeast Asia and East Asia .
Linnaeus introduced the name Crataegus oxyacantha for a species of Northern European Hawthorn and the name gradually became used for several similar species which were assumed to be the same , particularly the Midland Hawthorn C. laevigata and the Common Hawthorn C. monogyna .

The Kivu giant pouched rat ( Cricetomys kivuensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Neocallia pubescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neocallia .
Dioscorea floridana the Florida yam , is a plant species native to Florida , Alabama , Georgia and South Carolina .
Fisherostylus bruneri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Fisherostylus .
Cosoryx furcatus is an extinct species of antilocaprid that lived in the Miocene of Nevada .
Rewaconodon tikiensis is an extinct species of synapsid which existed in India during the upper Triassic period , the only species in the genus Rewaconodon .
Nebria mellyi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Russia .
Fritillaria dajinensis is an Asian species of herbaceous plant in the lily family , native to Sichuan Province in China .
The Japanese rhinoceros beetle , Japanese horned beetle , or kabutomushi ( カブトムシ ) , Allomyrina dichotoma , is a species of rhinoceros beetle .
Eoserranus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Danian stage of the Paleocene epoch .
Carolus Linnaeus , the Swedish naturalist who defined taxonomic arrangements for the animal , plant , and mineral kingdoms acquired samples of the sawtoothed grain beetle from Suriname ( Dutch Guiana ) and named the species `` Oryzaephilus surinamensis '' because of this .
Lorandersonia , commonly called rabbitbush , is a genus of North American flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Phrynobatrachus albomarginatus is a species of frog in the Phrynobatrachidae family .
Megachile polychroma is a species of bee in the family Megachilidae .
Setarches is a genus of deep - sea bristly scorpionfishes .
The Araliaceae are a family of flowering plants , also known as the aralia family ( after its type genus Aralia ) or ivy family .
Tomato frogs are any of the three species of genus Dyscophus ( family Microhylidae ) :
Austrorossia mastigophora is a species of bobtail squid native to western , southern and eastern Africa , from Guinea and Somalia to the Cape of Good Hope .
Acanthoteuthis is a belemnite genus , a squid - like cephalopod with an internal shell from the Late Jurassic Epoch , related to modern coleoids .
Oritrophium is a genus of Mesoamerican and South American flowering plant in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Phagnalon is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family native to Europe , Asia , and North Africa .
Atrypa is a genus of brachiopod with shells round to short egg - shaped , covered with many fine radial ridges ( or costae ) , that split further out and growthlines perpendicular to the costae and 2 - 3 times wider spaced .
Obolella was a genus of Cambrian brachiopod .
The sole species , Needhamiella pumilio , is a small shrub that is endemic to Western Australia .
Heteroclinus perspicillatus , the Common weedfish , is a species of clinid native to southern Australia where it is found in seagrass beds and rocky reefs ( especially with kelp cover ) at depths of up to 10 metres ( 33 ft ) .
Coryanthes speciosa , the bat orchid , is a species of orchid found in Brazil , Colombia , Costa Rica , French Guiana , Guatemala , Guyana , Honduras , Mexico , Nicaragua , Panama , Peru , Suriname , Venezuela , the Caribbean and Belize .
Echinolittorina biangulata is a species of sea snail in the Indo - West Pacific Ocean , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Scenelloidea is an extinct superfamily of paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position ( Gastropoda or Monoplacophora ) .
Princaxelia jamiesoni is a species of amphipod crustacean described in 2010 .
Cyathea nigrolineata is a species of tree fern in the family Cyatheaceae .
Chasmosaurinae is a subfamily of ceratopsid dinosaurs .
Theriosuchus is an extinct genus of atoposaurid mesoeucrocodylian from the Late Jurassic of Europe , the Early Cretaceous of Asia and the Late Cretaceous of Romania .
Rhynchostele is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to Mexico , Central America and Venezuela .
The Curculionidae comprise the family of the `` true '' weevils ( or `` snout beetles '' ) .
Dussumieriidae is a family of clupeiform fishes popularly called the `` round herrings '' .
Xanthisma paradoxum is a plant species native to the `` Four Corners '' region where Colorado , Arizona , New Mexico and Utah meet .
Yinlong ( meaning `` hidden dragon '' ) is a genus of basal ceratopsian dinosaur from the Late Jurassic Period of central Asia .
Leptotyphlops brevissimus , or the Caqueta blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
The Salado Springs salamander ( Eurycea chisholmensis ) is a candidate species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Thecacera boyla is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Polyceridae .
Polygonum bolanderi is an uncommon California species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Bolander 's knotweed .
Phrynobatrachus ogoensis ( commonly known as Boulenger 's African river frog ) is a species of frog in the Petropedetidae family .
Palystes is a genus of huntsman spiders , commonly called rain spiders or lizard - eating spiders , occurring in Africa , India , Australia , and the Pacific .
Coloborhynchus spielbergi is a pterosaur species from the Aptian - age Romualdo Member of the Lower Cretaceous Santana Formation , of Barra do Jardim , Araripe Plateau , Ceará Province , Brazil .
The Sokoke pipit ( Anthus sokokensis ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Parablepharis kuhlii is a species of praying mantis found in India , Myanmar , Vietnam , Borneo , and Java .
Docolamia incisa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Docolamia .
Lacandonia schismatica is a species of mycoheterotrophic plants in the Triuridaceae .
Paspalum urvillei is a species of grass known by the common name Vasey 's grass , or Vaseygrass .
Boechera dispar is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name pinyon rockcress .
The Petrosiidae are a family of sponges containing these genera :
Notropis simus ( bluntnose shiner ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Crataegus putnamiana is a rare species of North American hawthorn derived from hybridization between a species in Crataegus series Coccineae and a species in series Dilatatae .
Ptychochromis loisellei is a species of cichlid from the Mahanara River basin north of Sambava in northeastern Madagascar .
Ophiopholis is a genus of brittle stars ( Ophiuroidea ) found in oceans worldwide from tropics to temperate regions .
Drosophila persimilis is a species of fruit fly that is a sister species to D. pseudoobscura , and was one of 12 fruitfly genomes sequenced for a large comparative study .
Diaphanidae is a taxonomic family of small sea snails , marine opisthobranch gastropod molluscs or micromollusks in the superfamily Diaphanoidea , the headshield slugs and bubble snails .
Panax ginseng , the Chinese ginseng , is a species of ginseng .
Oecia oecophila is a moth of the Autostichidae family and only species in the Oecia genus .
Myctophum nitidulum , common name pearly lanternfish , is a species of deep sea fish in the family Myctophidae , the `` lanternfish '' .
Mesonerilla prospera is a species of invertebrate in the Nerillidae family endemic to Bermuda .
Similonedine brunniofasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Similonedine .
Urobatis is a genus of the family Urotrygonidae .
Sagda triptycha is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Sagdidae .
Ipomoea indica is a species of flowering plant in the family Convolvulaceae , known by several common names , including blue morning glory , oceanblue morning glory , koali awa , and blue dawn flower .
Achistrum is an extinct genus of sea cucumber which existed in Poland during the Triassic period , and the United States during the Carboniferous period .
Chonerhinos naritus is a species of freshwater pufferfish native to Southeast Asia .
Parator zonatus is a species of cyprinid fish found in the Zhujiang River in China and Vietnam .
Chaenactis artemisiifolia , with the common name White pincushion , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Although little is known about the species ' ecology , due to its deep water nature and its lack of known use in commercial trade , the IUCN redlist currently lists Synaphobranchus oregoni as Least Concern .
Sturisoma brevirostre is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Içá River basin .
Hakea mitchellii , commonly known as Desert Hakea , is a shrub species in the family Proteaceae .
Pentaphylax is a genus of flowering plants , with one or two species which are shrubs and small trees .
Bruniaceae is a family of shrubs native to the cape region of South Africa .
Koreaceratops is a genus of basal ceratopsian dinosaur discovered in Albian - age Lower Cretaceous rocks of South Korea .
Cattleya perrinii , commonly known as the Perrin 's Sophronitis , is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Brazil .
Ciliopagurus major is a species of hermit crab native to French Polynesia .
Prunus bifrons is a species of Prunus native to temperate and tropical Asia .
Sinployea youngi was a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Charopidae .
Draco indochinensis , commonly known as the Indo - Chinese flying lizard , is a species of agamid lizard endemic to South - east Asia .
Brachypylina is a suborder of oribatid mites .
Liocranidae is a family of araneomorph spiders , consisting of about 160 species of wandering spiders in 30 or so genera .
Dendrobium heterocarpum , the Different - fruited Dendrobium , is a species of orchid .
Mezirinae is a subfamily of Flat bug .
Copadichromis borleyi is a species of cichlid fish endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
The Hylocereeae are a tribe of cacti .
Holodiscus dumosus is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names rockspiraea , bush oceanspray , mountain spray , and glandular oceanspray .
Gnaphalium palustre , known by the common name western marsh cudweed , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Incilius perplexus ( common name : confusing toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Odixia is a genus of Tasmanian flowering plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Angaria melanacantha , common name the black - tankard angaria , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Angariidae .
Osgood 's rat ( Rattus osgoodi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Misionella is a genus of crevice weaver spiders .
Pycnosteus is an extinct genus of jawless fish from the Devonian .
Vaccinium stamineum , commonly known as deerberry , tall deerberry , squaw huckleberry , highbush huckleberry , buckberry , and southern gooseberry , is a species of flowering plant in the heath family .
Lotus hamatus is a species of legume known by the common name San Diego bird's - foot trefoil .
Western white pine ( Pinus monticola ) also called silver pine , and California mountain pine , in the family Pinaceae , is a species of pine that occurs in the mountains of the western United States and Canada , specifically the Sierra Nevada , the Cascade Range , the Coast Range , and the northern Rocky Mountains .
Ribes victoris is an uncommon North American species of currant known by the common name Victor 's gooseberry .
Calyptranthes luquillensis ( also called Luquillo Forest Lidflower ) is a species of plant in the Myrtaceae family .
Jocara marchiana is a species of snout moth found in Guatemala .
Allium yosemitense is a California species of wild onion known by the common name Yosemite onion .
Aetobarbakinoides is an extinct genus of stagonolepidid aetosaur known from the Late Triassic of Rio Grande do Sul state , southern Brazil .
Dicynodontia was later ranked as a suborder or infraorder with the larger group Anomodontia , which is classified as an order .
Causus lichtensteinii is a venomous viper species endemic to western and central Africa .
Geranium oreganum is a species of geranium known by the common name Oregon cranesbill , or Oregon geranium .
Synodontis punctifer is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Ivory Coast where it occurs in the Nzo and Bandama Rivers .
Salix gilgiana is a species of willow native to Japan and Korea .
Malacoctenus triangulatus , the Saddled blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny fish native to the Atlantic Ocean as well as the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean Sea from southern Florida to the coast of Brazil .
Arctostaphylos silvicola is a species of manzanita known by the common names Bonny Doon or silverleaf manzanita .
Cyanea stictophylla is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Kaiholena cyanea .
Microsauge bistrialis is a species of snout moth in the genus Microsauge .
Banksia scabrella , commonly known as the Burma Road Banksia , is a species of woody shrub in the genus Banksia .
Gamochaeta antarctica , the Antarctic Cudweed , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Penstemon grahamii , known by the common names Uinta Basin beardtongue and Graham 's beardtongue , is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family .
Haplochrois theae is a species of moth of the Elachistidae family .
Coreocalamobius parantennatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Coreocalamobius .
Scissurella bountyensis is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Scissurellidae .
Aspidites melanocephalus , commonly known as the black - headed python , is a species of snake in the family Pythonidae ( the python family ) .
Naja christyi ( formerly Boulengerina christyi ) , commonly known as the Congo water cobra or Christy 's water cobra , is a species of venomous snake belonging to the Elapidae family , and native to Sub - Saharan Africa .
Anabasis eugeniae , Eugenia 's anabasis , is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family .
Dalcerina tijucana is a moth in the Dalceridae family , and the only species in the genus Dalcerina .
Paphinia cristata is a species of the orchid genus Paphinia and the type species of this genus .
Shunosaurus , meaning `` Shu Lizard '' , is a genus of sauropod dinosaur from Middle Jurassic ( Bathonian -- Callovian ) beds in Sichuan Province in China , 170 million years ago .
The Fidicinini ( Boulard & Martinelli , 1996 ) are a tribe of cicadas .
Steatoda grossa , commonly known as the cupboard spider , the dark comb - footed spider , the brown house spider ( in Australia ) , or the false black widow ( though several other species are known by these names ) , is a common species of spider in the genus Steatoda .
Ctenosaura palearis , commonly known as the Guatemalan spiny - tailed iguana , is a species of spiny - tailed iguana endemic to the Motagua Valley , Guatemala .
Orthotylus troodensis is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that is endemic to Cyprus .
Geotrypetes pseudoangeli is a species of amphibian in the Dermophiidae family found in Guinea and Liberia .
Neduba is a genus of insects in the family Tettigoniidae ( katydids ) .
Lilium tsingtauense ( also known as `` Twilight Lily '' ) is an East Asian species of plants in the lily family .
Lobelia nicotianifolia is a species of flowering plant with a distribution primarily across India and Sri Lanka .
Balanetta is a genus of small , often colorful , sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the taxonomic family of the margin shells ( Marginellidae ) .
Glycosmis pentaphylla is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae , known commonly as orangeberry and gin berry .
Alburnoides bipunctatus , known vernacularly as the schneider , spirlin , bleak , riffle minnow , and others , is a species of small ( 9-cm average length ) freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Rhacophorus arboreus ( commonly known as the forest green tree frog , モリアオガエル in Japanese ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to Japan .
Conraua beccarii is a species of frog in the Conrauidae family found in Eritrea and Ethiopia .
Epiactaeodes is a genus of crabs in the family Xanthidae , containing the following species :
Faucaria tigrina is a species of succulent plant in the Aizoaceae family .
Clausilia bidentata , the ' Two Toothed Door Snail ' is a species of door snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the genus Clausilia belonging to the family Clausiliidae , all of which have a clausilium .
Ancipitia is a genus of orchids originating from South America , currently consisting of 28 species .
Cordaitaceae is an extinct family of conifers .
Otopappus is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family , primarily Mesoamerican but with one species from Jamaica .
Abrotocrinus is an extinct genus of crinoids .
Lilioceris cheni , the air potato leaf beetle , is a species of beetle in the Lilioceris genus that feeds on air potato plants .
Trochaclis calva is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ataphridae , the pyrams and their allies .
Cyathea edanoi is a species of tree fern endemic to Luzon in the Philippines , where it grows in montane forest at an altitude of about 1300 m. The trunk is erect and 1 - -2 m tall .
Pseudomugil paskai , commonly known as Paska 's blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Pomaulax japonicus , the Japanese star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Anthrenus flavipes is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae known by the common name furniture carpet beetle .
Encheloclarias curtisoma is a species of airbreathing catfish endemic to Malaysia where it is only known from Selangor .
Didelta is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1786 .
Emblemariopsis pricei , the Seafan blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in Glover 's Reef , on the coasts of Belize and Honduras , in the western Atlantic ocean .
Meca astralis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Meca .
Glyceridae is a family of polychaete worms .
The armored marstonia , scientific name Marstonia pachyta , also known as Pyrgulopsis pachyta , is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Chrysobatrachus cupreonitens is a species of frogs in the Hyperoliidae family ; it is monotypic within the genus Chrysobatrachus .
Unatara atinga is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Unatara .
Senoculus darwini is a spider species in the genus Senoculus found in Argentina .
Gandalfus yunohana is a species of crab found on hydrothermal vents on the eastern edge of the Philippine Sea Plate south of Japan .
Trite planiceps is a common jumping spider endemic to New Zealand and one of about 150 species of jumping spiders in New Zealand .
Gramma brasiliensis is a species of basslet endemic to the Atlantic coast of Brazil where it is a reef inhabitant .
Otothyris juquiae is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Ribeira de Iguape River basin .
Peloridium hammoniorum is a species of moss bug from southern South America , and is the only known species in the genus Peloridium .
Radiodactylus is an extinct genus of non - azhdarchid azhdarchoid pterosaur known from the Early Cretaceous of Texas , southern United States .
Juncus planifolius is a species of rush , commonly known as broadleaf rush , broad - leaved rush , or grass - leaved rush .
Coloborhynchus clavirostris is a pterosaur species in the family Ornithocheiridae , known from the Lower Cretaceous of England ( Albian age , 98 million years ago ) .
Turbo militaris , common name the military turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
The Colombian chachalaca ( Ortalis columbiana ) is a species of bird in the Cracidae family .
The South American tapir ( Tapirus terrestris ) , Brazilian tapir ( from the Tupi tapi'ira ) , lowland tapir or ( in Portuguese ) anta , is one of five species in the tapir family , along with the Mountain tapir , the Malayan tapir , the Baird 's tapir , and the kabomani tapir .
The North - Chinese leopard ( Panthera pardus japonensis ) , also known as North China leopard , is a leopard subspecies native to northern China .
Galactomyia is a subgenus of tachinid flies , commonly known as the feather - legged flies or hairy - legged flies .
Clostridium indolis was originally named for its ability to hydrolyze tryptophan to indole , pyruvate , and ammonia in the classic indole test which is used to distinguish bacterial species .
Pinus lumholtzii , the Lumholtz 's pine or pino triste ( ' sad pine ' in Spanish ) , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Naraoiidae is a family , of extinct , soft - shelled trilobite - like arthropods , that belongs to the order Nectaspida .
Syncarida is a superorder of crustaceans , comprising the two extant orders Anaspidacea and Bathynellacea , and the extinct order Palaeocaridacea .
Triviidae is a taxonomic family of small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Streptomyces hiroshimensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil .
Hopea polyalthioides is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae .
Agonum is a large genus of ground beetles in the subfamily Harpalinae , tribe Platynini .
The Tien Shan dhole ( Cuon alpinus hesperius ) , also known as the Siberian wild dog , Western Asiatic dhole , or Northern dhole is a possible subspecies of dhole native to the Altai and Tien Shan mountain ranges , and possibly Pamir and Kashmir .
Adansonia digitata ( baobab ) is the most widespread of the Adansonia species , and is native to the African continent .
Chrysothamnus scopulorum called Grand Canyon glowweed or evening - daisy , is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Afifella is a photoheterotrophic genus in the phylum Proteobacteria ( Bacteria ) .
Millepora alcicornis , or sea ginger , is a species of colonial fire coral with a calcareous skeleton .
Epirochroides hovanus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Epirochroides .
Leptotyphlops drewesi , or Drewes ' worm snake , is a species of snake in the family Leptotyphlopidae .
Lysapsus caraya is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in central and southern Brazil .
The Kauai island - aster or Kauai hesperomannia ( Hesperomannia lydgatei ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
Nyctibatrachus minimus is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family .
Vertigo alpestris is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs or micromollusks in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Chiloglanis carnosus is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it occurs in rapids of the lower Congo River .
The Arthrorhaphidaceae are a family of lichenized fungi in the division Ascomycota .
Cylindropuntia abyssi , common name Peach Springs cholla , is a species of cactus endemic to northwestern Arizona .
Tachysphex is a very large genus of wasps in the family Crabronidae , consisting of over 400 species .
Astragalus wetherillii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Wetherill 's milkvetch .
Mimulus cusickii is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Cusick 's monkeyflower .
Romneya coulteri , the Coulter 's Matilija poppy or Californian tree poppy , is a species of flowering plant in the poppy family .
Conocephalus is a genus of bush - cricket , known as coneheads ( a term also applied to members of the related genus Ruspolia ) .
Tuber melanosporum , called the black truffle , Périgord truffle or French black truffle , is a species of truffle native to Southern Europe .
Vertigo ovata , common name the ovate vertigo , is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Inula spiraeifolia is a European species perennial herbaceous plant belonging to the genus Inula within the daisy family .
Hymenocallis howardii is a species of spider - lily , native to southwestern Mexico .
Epidendrum brevivenium is a species of Epidendrum Orchid native to Peru and the provinces of Pichincha , Napo , and Tungurahua in Ecuador at altitudes of 2.8 to 3.4 km .
The Spongillidae are a family of sponges that live in freshwater lakes .
Asclepias erosa is a species of milkweed known commonly as desert milkweed .
Lotus benthamii is a species of legume known by the common name Bentham 's broom .
Hieracium attenboroughianum , or Attenborough 's hawkweed , is a species of hawkweed in the genus Hieracium , found only in the Brecon Beacons in south Wales .
Arizonerpeton is an extinct genus of nectridean lepospondyl .
Porteresia coarctata is considered by some botanists to be the only species in the genus Porteresia .
Tuberolabium is a genus of epiphytic flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
× Myrtgerocactus lindsayi is a species of cacti , the only one in the hybrid genus × Myrtgerocactus .
Sedum oregonense is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family known by the common name cream stonecrop .
Maladera is a genus in the beetle family Scarabaeidae , containing species such as Maladera insanabilis and Maladera castanea .
Eophrynus prestvicii is an extinct species arachnids belonging to the order Trigonotarbida .
Delta conoideum , the Mason wasp , is a species of potter wasp in the subfamily Eumeninae of the family Vespidae .
Benthophiloides brauneri is a species of goby , a benthophilic fish native to the fresh and brackish waters of the Black Sea , the Caspian Sea and the Sea of Azov as well as their surrounding rivers and estuaries .
Arganiella exilis is a species of very small freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic operculate gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Pentaceraster cumingi , sometimes known as the Panamic cushion star , Cortez starfish or knobby star ( a name also used for other species ) , is a species of starfish in the family Oreasteridae .
Emathis weyersi is a species of jumping spider that occurs from Sumatra to the Philippines .
Apteronotus galvisi is a species of ghost knifefish that was first described in a 2007 scientific paper .
Martinavis is a genus of enantiornithine birds which existed in what is now southern France , North America and Salta Province , Argentina during the late Cretaceous period .
The Milesiini ( or Xylotini ) is a large and diverse tribe of hoverflies .
Conus achatinus , common name the turtle cone or the agate cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Tephritis formosa is a species of tephritid fly .
Described by Tschitscherine in 1900 , it is the only species in the genus Bothynoproctus .
Papilio multicaudata , the two - tailed swallowtail , is a species of the family Papilionidae found in western North America from British Columbia to Central America .
Trebacosa brunhesi is a wolf spider species in the genus Trebacosa found in France .
The San Joaquin antelope squirrel or Nelson 's antelope squirrel ( Ammospermophilus nelsoni ) , is a species of antelope squirrel , in the San Joaquin Valley of the U.S. state of California .
Clypeola elegans is a plant species in the genus Clypeola .
Urotrichini is a taxonomic tribe of the mole family , and consists of Japanese and American shrew - moles .
The genus Bathmochoffatia ( basal choffatia ) was named by Hahn G. and Hahn R. in 1998 .
Rhabdophis is a genus of snakes , generally called keelback snakes , found primarily in southeast Asia .
Galenia secunda ( onesided galenia ) is a plant species native to South Africa but naturalized in Australia ( Western Australia , Victoria , Tasmania and New South Wales ) , Spain , and the United States ( Florida and New Jersey ) .
Polemon collaris , or the collared snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Pteronymia is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Arthur Gardiner Butler and Druce in 1872 .
Agalychnis is a genus of tree frogs native to forests in Mexico , Central America and northwestern South America .
Hexeretmis is a genus of moth in the Alucitidae family .
Aspasia lunata is a species of orchid , native to tropical South America , in the Brazilian southeast and south and reaching Bolivia and Paraguay , from 200 - -750 metres ( 660 - -2,460 ft ) in elevation .
The keeled slug - eating snake , Pareas carinatus , is a species of snake in the Colubridae family .
Coenobita scaevola is a species of terrestrial hermit crab from the western Indian Ocean and Red Sea .
Bidensovirus is a genus of single stranded DNA viruses that infect invertebrates .
Glinus radiatus is a species of flowering plant in the family Molluginaceae known by the common name spreading sweetjuice .
Ostenoteuthidae is an extinct family of cephalopods from Lower Jurassic of Italy .
Turanoceratops ( `` Turan horned face '' ) is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur from the late Cretaceous Bissekty Formation of Uzbekistan .
Callicopris cerograpta is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Callicopris .
Teleogryllus oceanicus , commonly known as the black field cricket is a cricket species native to Australia .
Pseudohomaloptera tatereganii is a species of the genus Pseudohomaloptera in the family Balitoridae .
Ilex integerrima ( `` Soundest holly '' ) is a species of holly in the Aquifoliaceae family , native from Brazil and typically found in its Atlantic Forest vegetation .
Larus is a large genus of gulls with worldwide distribution ( although by far the greatest species diversity is in the Northern Hemisphere ) .
The Daraelitidae form a family in the ammonoid order Prolecanitida from the Upper Mississippian - Middle Permian characterized by discoidal shells with no prominent sculpture , moderately large umbilicus , and goniatitic or ceratitic sutures with a trifid ( three pronged ) ventral lobe and few auxiliary lobes .
Primula rosea , the Himalayan meadow primrose , is a flowering plant species in the genus Primula .
Euproserpinus is a genus of sphinx moth in the Sphingidae family .
The Zambian mole - rat ( Fukomys amatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Bathyergidae .
Pseudochazara pelopea ( Klug , 1832 ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Zeugopterus is a genus of turbots native to the north Atlantic Ocean .
Laelia anceps is a species of orchid found in Mexico and Guatemala .
Penstemon scariosus is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name White River beardtongue .
Samolus ( known as brookweed , or water pimpernel ) is a widely distributed genus of about a dozen species of water - loving herbs .
The Calcinea are a subclass of the calcareous sponges .
Cissus bicolor is a species of vine .
Polyrhachis illaudata is a species of large ant found in Sri Lanka , India extending through Southeast Asia to the Philippines .
Pterodoras rivasi is a species of thorny catfish found in the Orinoco River basin of Colombia and Venezuela .
The Guadeloupe parakeet ( Psittacara labati ) might have been a species of parrot that was endemic to Guadeloupe .
Iuticosaurus ( meaning `` Jute lizard '' ) is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of the Isle of Wight .
Procambarus nechesae , sometimes called the Neches crayfish , is a species of crustacean in the family Cambaridae .
Sphaerioeme rubristerna is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Sphaerioeme .
Skimmia japonica , the Japanese skimmia , is a species of flowering plant in the family Rutaceae , native to Japan , China and south east Asia .
Opsilia chinensis is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family that is endemic to China .
Calanthe triplicata is a species of orchid native to Oceania , Asia , and the islands of eastern Africa .
Paeonia qiui is a species of peony very similar to P. jishanensis , but with more divided foliage .
Salvadora persica ( Arak , Galenia asiatica , Meswak , Peelu , Pīlu , Salvadora indica , or toothbrush tree , mustard tree , mustard bush ) , is a species of Salvadora .
Limonium bellidifolium , commonly known as the matted sea - lavender , is an aggregate species in the family Plumbaginaceae .
Paropsisterna selmani , the Tasmanian Eucalyptus Beetle , is a species of leaf beetle native to Tasmania which has been inadvertently introduced to the Republic of Ireland and United Kingdom .
Ctenopseustis fraterna , the brownheaded leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Cerocoma is a Palearctic genus of blister beetle , whose biology is poorly known .
Nuttall 's woodpecker ( Dryobates nuttallii ) is a species of woodpecker named after naturalist Thomas Nuttall in 1843 .
