Clinus brevicristatus , the Cape klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean around South Africa where it prefers habitats with plentiful growth of seaweed .
Opuntia pailana is a species of the genus Opuntia in the family of Cactaceae .
Anthracosuchus ( meaning `` coal crocodile '' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of dyrosaurid crocodyliform from the Paleocene of Colombia .
Gaoligongshania megalothyrsa is a species of small , bushy mountain bamboo , of the monotypic genus Gaoligongshania .
Vanda coerulea , commonly known as blue orchid , blue vanda or autumn lady 's tresses , is a species of orchid found in Assam and neighbouring Khasi hills with its range extending to China ( southern Yunnan ) .
Trifolium leibergii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Leiberg 's clover .
Agapanthia amicula is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that can be found only in Turkey .
Mauritia histrio , common name the harlequin cowry or the stage cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Cordylancistrus is a genus of suckermouth armored catfish native to South America .
Trema orientalis is a species of flowering tree in the hemp family , Cannabaceae .
Echmatemys is an extinct genus of geoemydid turtle from the Eocene of North America .
Naesiotus pilsbryi is a species of tropical air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Orthalicidae .
Trichomecyna fuscovittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichomecyna .
Anisophyllea is a genus of plant in the family Anisophylleaceae .
Eleutherodactylus cubanus is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family found in Cuba .
Iravadiidae is a family of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Rissooidea and the clade Littorinimorpha .
Calathus syriacus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found on Cyprus , in Ukraine and in southern part of Russia .
Charaxes usambarae is a member of the large species group Charaxes etheocles .
The Inconspicuous Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum inconspicuum ) is a species of orchid .
Romanzoffia californica is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name California mistmaiden .
Pataecus fronto , the Red Indianfish , is a species of Australian prowfish endemic to the coastal waters of western and southern Australia where it occurs at depths of from 40 to 80 metres ( 130 to 260 ft ) .
Alyxia lindii , commonly known as Alyxia Vine , is a species of climbing shrub in the Apocynaceae family .
Justicia rizzinii is a species of flowering plant in the family Acanthaceae , native to Brazil .
Leuconotopicus is a genus of woodpeckers in the ( family Picidae ) native to North and South America .
Mecochirus longimanatus is an extinct species of lobster - like decapod crustacean from the Jurassic of Europe .
Pultenaea is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae - Faboideae that are native to Australia .
Heterocyclus perroquini is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Hydrobiidae .
Heterocharax is a genus of characins from South America , with three currently described species :
Saurosphargis is an extinct genus of a basal marine reptile , saurosphargid , known from the Middle Triassic ( Anisian age ) of southwestern Poland and eastern Netherlands .
It contains the single species Hobapromea cleta , which is found in Australia ( Queensland ) .
Bolboporites is an extinct genus of conical echinoderm that lived in the Ordovician of Europe and North America .
Draba aizoides is a species of Draba , known as yellow whitlow - grass .
Lyophyllum is a genus of about 40 species of fungi , widespread in north temperate regions .
The Laelapidae are a family of mites in the order Mesostigmata .
Lophophora diffusa , commonly known as false peyote , is a species of plant in the Cactaceae family and one of the only two species in the Lophophora genus .
Ceroxys similis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Ceroxys of the family Ulidiidae .
Gossypium is the cotton genus .
Parenchelyurus hepburni , Hepburn 's blenny or the Bluespotted blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian ocean .
Austrostipa is a primarily Australian genus of plants in the grass family , commonly called speargrass .
Cantharidus antipoda puysegurensis is a subspecies of marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top shells .
Maylandia hajomaylandi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from around Chisumulu Island .
Scleroderma citrinum , commonly known as the common earthball , pigskin poison puffball , or common earth ball , is the most common species of earthball in the UK and occurs widely in woods , heathland and in short grass from Autumn to Winter .
Thelephora anthocephala is a species of coral fungus in the family Thelephoraceae .
Pyura spinifera , commonly called the sea tulip , is a species of sessile ascidian that lives in coastal waters at depths of up to 80 m ( 260 feet ) .
Carex phaeocephala is a species of sedge known by the common name dunhead sedge .
Macrocyclops albidus is a larvivorous copepod species .
Sericomyia militaris is a North American species of flower fly or hoverfly .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Plurisperma dalbergiae .
Cypella elegans is a herbaceous plant species in the genus Cypella endemic to Jujuy Province in northwestern Argentina .
Oligopygoida is an extinct order of irregular echinoids .
Aphonopelma paloma , or the Paloma dwarf , is a species of spider belonging to the family Theraphosidae .
Axinandra zeylanica is a species of plant in the Crypteroniaceae family .
Uvularia puberula , the mountain bellwort , is a plant species native to the eastern United States .
Ehrharta calycina is a species of grass known by the common names perennial veldtgrass and purple veldtgrass .
Plagiolepis ampeloni is a species of ant in genus Plagiolepis .
Paraenhydrocyon josephi ( `` beside Enhydrocyon '' ) is an extinct species of the genus Paraenhydrocyon , a somewhat small bone crushing omnivorous mammal similar to a dog of the family Canidae which inhabited North America during the Oligocene living from 33.3 - -20.6 Ma and existed for approximately 12.7 million years .
Salix orestera is a species of willow known by the common name Sierra willow , or gray - leafed Sierra willow .
Paysonia lyrata is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name lyreleaf bladderpod .
Protonibea diacanthus , commonly known as the blackspotted croaker , is a species of fish native to the Indo - Pacific region .
Ficus religiosa or sacred fig is a species of fig native to Indian subcontinent , south - west China and Indochina .
Papilio pelodurus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Malawi , Tanzania and Zambia .
The Baer pugolovka ( Benthophilus baeri ) is a species of goby widespread in the southern and central Caspian Sea , to Lenkoran in south .
Argidae is a large family of sawflies , containing some 800 species worldwide , primarily in tropical regions .
Rhododendron lapponicum ( Lapland rosebay , 高山杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species found in subarctic regions around the world , where it grows at altitudes ranging from sea level to 1900 meters .
Carabus alexandrae subidolon is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family that is endemic to Gansu , China .
Enriquebeltrania crenatifolia is a plant species of the family Euphorbiaceae endemic to the Yucatán Peninsula in Southeastern Mexico ( States of Campeche , Quintana Roo , and Yucatán ) .
Chamaesipho columna is the type species for the barnacle genus Chamaesipho .
Mallotus pleiogynus is a species of the spurge family ( Euphorbiaceae ) .
Dryopteris crassirhizoma is a fern species in the genus Dryopteris .
Galium microphyllum ( bracted bedstraw ) is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family .
The Strickland 's woodpecker ( Leuconotopicus stricklandi ) is a medium - sized species of woodpecker endemic to Mexico .
Microtralia insularis is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Ellobiidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Endoscypha perforans .
Prenanthella is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the daisy family containing the single species Prenanthella exigua , which is known by the common name brightwhite .
The Junín canastero ( Asthenes virgata ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Kurtus indicus , the Indian humphead , is a species of nurseryfish native to fresh , brackish , and marine waters of the coastal regions of southern Asia from India to southeast China and Indonesia .
Chaetodon guentheri or the Crotchet butterflyfish is a fish species in the genus Chaetodon , and is native to The western pacific ocean near Taiwan .
Cariblatta lutea is a small species of cockroach native to the United States and other countries , measuring usually around 7 millimeters long as an adult and under 2 millimeters from head tip to abdomen tip at the 1st instar or hatchling .
Densignathus is an extinct genus of early tetrapod from the Late Devonian of Pennsylvania in the United States .
Taphozous is a genus of sac - winged bat - one commonly called a tomb bat - in the family Emballonuridae .
Diectomis is a genus of tropical plants in the grass family .
Campanula cochleariifolia ( also Campanula cochlearifolia ) , common name earleaf bellflower or fairy's - thimble , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Campanula of the family Campanulaceae , native to the Pyrenees , Alps , and Carpathian Mountains of Central Europe .
Rhododendron watsonii ( 无柄杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to southern Gansu and western Sichuan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2500 - -3000 meters .
Columnaria is an extinct genus of rugose coral that lived from the Late Ordovician to the Late Devonian .
Pradosia decipiens is a species of plant in the Sapotaceae family endemic to Brazil .
Clematis socialis is a rare species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Alabama leather flower .
Paphinia lindeniana is a species of orchid native to Colombia , Venezuela , Brazil , Peru and possibly Guyana .
Lygosoma is a genus of lizards , commonly known as writhing skinks , which are members of the family Scincidae .
Bryonympha silvana is a moth of the Immidae family and only species in the Bryonympha genus .
Paeonia kesrouanensis is a species of peony native to Syria , Turkey and Lebanon .
Tremarctos is a genus of the family Ursidae , subfamily Tremarctinae endemic to Americas from the Pliocene to recent .
Elapsoidea is a genus of venomous elapid snakes commonly known as venomous garter snakes or African garter snakes .
Synoplotherium ( also known as `` Dromocyon '' ) is an extinct genus of relatively small , wolf - like mesonychids that lived 50 million years ago , in what is now Wyoming .
Pitcairnia devansayana is a species of plant in the Bromeliaceae family .
Hibbertopterus is a genus of giant sea scorpion ( order Eurypterida ) that inhabited the swamps of Scotland during the Carboniferous .
Hoplophorus was an extinct genus of glyptodont , a family of mammals related to armadillo .
Nebria nudicollis is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Algeria .
The Two - humped Dendrobium ( Dendrobium bigibbum ) is a species of orchid .
Parcoblatta zebra , the banded wood cockroach , is a species of Parcoblatta native to the United States .
Scalopodontes is an extinct genus of therocephalian which existed in Russia during the upper Permian period .
Clupanodon thrissa , the Chinese gizzard shad , is a species of gizzard shad occurring from Korea to Thailand and possibly the Philippines .
Xyliphius lepturus is a species of banjo catfish found in Colombia , Ecuador and Venezuela where it can be found in the upper Amazon and Orinoco River basins .
Allobates mcdiarmidi ( common name : McDiarmid 's rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Gyroscala lamellosa , common name : the lamellose wentletrap , is a species of medium - sized predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Epitoniidae , the wentletraps .
Platykotta akaina is a species of decapod crustacean from the Triassic of the United Arab Emirates .
Herina frondescentiae is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae It is wetland species of about 3 - -4 millimetres ( 0.12 - -0.16 in ) in length .
Poa infirma is a species of grass known by the common names early meadow - grass and weak bluegrass .
Aquifex is a genus of bacteria , one of the few in the phylum Aquificae .
Mesorhizobium plurifarium is a species of root nodule bacteria first isolated from Acacia species in Senegal .
Aeshna viridis , the green hawker , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Chrysothamnus viscidiflorus is a North American species of shrub in the daisy family known by the common names yellow rabbitbrush and green rabbitbrush .
Heteropogon is a genus of annual and perennial plants in the grass family known generally as tangleheads , widespread primarily in tropical and subtropical regions .
Brodiaea santarosae is a rare Brodiaea species known by the common name Santa Rosa brodiaea and Santa Rosa Basalt brodiaea .
Porcellana sayana is a species of porcelain crab that lives in the western Atlantic Ocean , often as a commensal of hermit crabs .
Froesia gereauana is a plant species endemic to the State of Amazonas in southern Venezuela .
Palaeochiropteryx ( /ˌpæliːoʊkaɪˈrɒptərɨks/ PAL - ee - oh - ky - ROP - tər - iks ) is an extinct genus of bat from the Middle Eocene of Europe .
Vasum cassiforme , common name the helmet vase , is a species of medium to large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinellidae .
Amphoricarpos is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1847 .
Hallaxa decorata is a species of sea slug or dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Actinocyclidae .
Nocardia farcinica is a species of bacteria and a member of the genus Nocardia .
Mystus nigriceps , the two - spot catfish , is a species of catfish of the family Bagridae .
Parapolytretus rugosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parapolytretus .
Struthiosaurinae is a subfamily of ankylosaurian dinosaurs from the Cretaceous of Europe .
Latirus gibbulus , common name the gibbose latirus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Haplothrips is a genus of Phlaeothripid thrips .
Herreriopsis is a genus of one species of flowering plants , endemic to Madagascar .
Poirieria zelandica , common name the spiny murex , is a species of large predatory sea snail with an operculum .
Pachythamnus is a genus of Mesoamerican flowering plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Epinephelus labriformis , commonly called starry grouper or flag cabrilla among various other vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Lysicarpus is a genus of tree in the family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1858 .
Asteroxylon ( `` star - shaped xylem '' ) is an extinct genus of plants of the Division Lycopodiophyta known from anatomically preserved specimens in an Early Devonian deposit of chert at Rhynie , Aberdeenshire in North - East Scotland that has been dated at 396 ± 8 million years ago .
Kleinia galpinii is a species of the genus Kleinia and family Asteraceae .
Harpa harpa , common name the true harp , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Harpidae , the harp snails .
Jarilinus is an extinct genus of chroniosuchid reptiliomorph from upper Permian ( upper Tatarian age ) deposits of Novgorod and Orenburg Region , Russia .
Cinara confinis , the black stem aphid , is a species of aphid in the genus Cinara , found feeding on the twigs of various species of fir ( Abies ) and on several other species of coniferous trees .
Typhlops is a genus of blind snakes found in Europe , Africa , Asia and Central and South America .
Pinicola is a genus of `` grosbeaks '' of the finch family , Fringillidae , containing a single species , the pine grosbeak ( Pinicola enucleator ) .
Bistorta officinalis , commonly known as bistort or European bistort , is a species of flowering plants in the dock family Polygonaceae , previously included in the genera Polygonum or Persicaria .
Primapus is an extinct genus of apodiform bird from the Early Eocene of the United Kingdom .
Calloodes grayianus , the Golden bordered beetle , is a species of shining leaf chafers belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Naravelia laurifolia is a species of vine in the Ranunculaceae family .
Ferocactus glaucescens ( glaucous barrel cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cactaceae .
Dermacentor albipictus , the winter tick , is a species of hard tick that is an external parasite of moose ( Alces alces ) in North America .
Labrisomus xanti , the Largemouth blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Mexico from Sebastián Vizcaíno Bay , Baja California to Bahía Tenacatita , Jalisco .
Benthophilus casachicus is a species of goby widespread along the eastern coasts of the Caspian Sea from the Cape Pischanyi to Ogurja Ada at south , also near Astrakhan .
Cychrus attenuatus is a species of beetle from a Carabidae family , that is endemic to Europe .
Chrysomya villeneuvi , or Hairy Maggot , is a South East Asian fly species of forensic importance because the Hairy maggots of this species have been collected from human corpses .
Temnothorax americanus is a species of slave - maker ant in the genus Temnothorax .
Risor ruber , the Tusked goby , is a species of goby native to reefs of the western Atlantic Ocean from southern Florida to the Bahamas and south to northern Brazil .
Gastrochilus kadooriei is a species of Gastrochilus .
Beaufortia polylepis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Beaufortia .
Assiminea palauensis is a species of minute , salt marsh snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk , or micromollusks , in the family Assimineidae .
Anoda is a genus of flowering plants in the mallow family .
The Cicadinae are a subfamily of cicadas , containing the translucent cicadas .
Scirpus congdonii is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name Congdon 's bulrush after noted Californian botanist J.W. Congdon .
Nidularium scheremetiewii is a species of bromeliad in the genus Nidularium .
Acrobasis sylviella , the ironwood tubemaker moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Acrobasis .
Labeo alluaudi is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae , the carps and minnows .
Iotrochota birotulata , the green finger sponge , is a species of demosponge in the phylum Porifera .
Champsosaurus is an extinct genus of diapsid reptile belonging to the order Choristodera .
Streptomyces albiflavescens is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from rainforest areas in the Yunnan Province in the south west of China .
Picea neoveitchii ( Chinese : 大果青扦 ) is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Lachenalia reflexa , commonly known as yellow soldier , is species of the genus Lachenalia native to South Africa .
Herina paludum is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in most of Europe .
Taphrina deformans infects species of the genus Prunus ( including P. amygdalus ( almond ) and P. persica ( peach ) ) .
Psalteriomonas is a genus of amoebae in the group of Heterolobosea .
The type species is Lonchognathosaurus acutirostris .
Afropsipyla pictella is a species of snout moth in the genus Afropsipyla .
The Jagath Gunawardena 's shrub frog , ( Pseudophilautus jagathgunawardanai ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Hoshihananomia transsylvanica is a species of beetle in the Hoshihananomia genus that is in the Mordellidae family , which is a part of the Tenebrionoidea superfamily .
Myrmica lonae is a species of ants distributed across South , Central and North Europe , East Europe , Asia Minor , the Caucasus , West Siberian Plain and Northern Kazakhstan .
Coelioxys rufitarsis is a species of leaf - cutting bee in the subgenus Boreocoelioxys within the genus Coelioxys .
Zabrus aegaeus is a species ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that is endemic to Greece .
Stachys manantlanensis is a plant species endemic to the Mexican State of Jalisco .
Ventichthys biospeedoi , the East Pacific vent - brotula , is a species of cusk - eel found around thermal vents on the SouthEast Pacific Rise at depths of about 2,586 metres ( 8,484 ft ) This species grows to a length of 28.2 centimetres ( 11.1 in ) SL .
Quercus vulcanica , the Kasnak Oak , is a rare Turkish species of tree found only in a few locations in western and south - central Turkey .
Hygrophorus nemoreus is an edible species of fungus in the genus Hygrophorus .
Papilio mechowianus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Angola and Congo Republic .
Anisocarpus is a genus of flowering plants in the tarweed tribe within the daisy family .
It was described by Kielan in 1960 , and the type species in Eodindymene pulchra , which was originally described under the genus Dindymene by Olin in 1906 .
It contains the single species Birgorima pulchripicta , which is found in Sarawak .
Tetronarce macneilli also known as the Shortail torpedo is a species of large electric ray .
Lachesilla rossica is a rare psocopteran species described from Southern Russia .
Tegula lividomaculata , common name the West Indian tegula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Branta thessaliensis is a prehistoric species of black goose known from fossils found in Greece .
Priobium is a genus of wood - boring , death - watch beetles ranging in western distribution in North America .
Ypsilorchis is a genus of plants endemic to southern China .
Albertochampsa is an extinct genus of globidontan alligatoroid from the Late Cretaceous of Alberta .
Ruminococcus is a genus of bacteria in the class Clostridia .
Archaeoattacus staudingeri is a species of moth in the Archaeoattacus genus found on the Malay Peninsula and on Borneo .
Theba arinagae is a species of land snail in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Marine angelfish are perciform fish of the family Pomacanthidae .
Solidago elongata , commonly called West Coast Canada goldenrod or Cascade Canada goldenrod , is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Zostera novazelandica Setchell is a species of seagrass in the family Zosteraceae occurring on the shores of New Zealand .
Calliostoma katherina is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae , the calliostoma top snails .
Alosternida chalybaea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Alosternida .
The Sesiidae or clearwing moths are a family of the Lepidoptera in most species of which the wings partially have hardly any of the normal lepidopteran scales , leaving them transparent .
Achnatherum diegoense is a species of grass known by the common name San Diego needlegrass .
Cicindela albissima , commonly called the Coral Pink Sand Dunes tiger beetle is a species of tiger beetle endemic to Coral Pink Sand Dunes State Park in southern Utah , United States .
Leucosphaerina is a genus of fungi in the Hypocreales order .
Paysonia stonensis ( syn . Lesquerella stonensis ) is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Stones River bladderpod .
Amorphoscelis pulchella is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Uganda , Zimbabwe and the Congo River region .
Nemuroglanis is a genus of three - barbeled catfishes .
It contains the single genus Gasterella , which in turn contains the single species Gasterella luteophila , found in the USA .
Pantosperma holochalca is a species of sedge moths , and the only species in the genus Pantosperma .
Oenosaurus is an extinct genus of sphenodontian reptile from the Late Jurassic of Germany .
Nassarius olivaceus , common name : the Olivaceous Nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Nolidae is a family of moths with about 1,400 described species worldwide .
Gracila albomarginata , the Masked Grouper , is a species of Groupers in the monotypic genus Gracila belonging to the Serranidae family .
Cyrtandra dentata is a rare species of flowering plant in the African violet family known by the common names mountain cyrtandra and sharp - toothed cyrtandra .
The Great Eggfly ( Hypolimnas bolina ) , also called the Blue Moon Butterfly in New Zealand or Common Eggfly , is a species of nymphalid butterfly .
Euphagus is a small genus of New World blackbirds .
Nebria kratteri is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Albania , Greece , Italy , and Republic of Macedonia .
Dodia kononenkoi kononenkoi ( Magadan region , Yukon territory ) Dodia kononenkoi sikhotensis Tshistjakov , 1988 ( Primorye : Sikhote - Alin ) Dodia transbaikalensis was described as a subspecies of Dodia kononenkoi , but is now mostly treated as a full species .
Eatoniella glacialis is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eatoniellidae , the eatoniellids .
Peperomia blanda , the arid - land peperomia , is a species of herb in the Piperaceae family .
Brachyscome angustifolia ( commonly known as the Stiff Daisy or Grassland Daisy ) is a pink or light purple species of daisy located in Australia , with a few in New Zealand and Papua New Guinea .
Berberidopsidales is an order of Southern Hemisphere woody flowering plants .
Erigeron grandiflorus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Rocky Mountain alpine fleabane and largeflower fleabane .
Castanea mollissima ( Chinese chestnut ) is a member of the family Fagaceae , and a species of chestnut native to China , Taiwan , and Korea .
It contains the single species Chrysaegliodes noliformis , which is found in Gabon .
Pseudoplectania nigrella , commonly known as the ebony cup , the black false plectania , or the hairy black cup , is a species of fungi in the family Sarcosomataceae .
Lanceacheyla whartoni is a species of mite in a monotypic genus in the family Cheyletidae .
Chrysopa perla , known commonly as the Green Lacewing , is a species of Neuropteran belonging to the family Chrysopidae ( subfamily Chrysopinae ) .
Opsilia malachitica is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family that can be found in Algeria , Spain , Morocco , Portugal , Sicily and Tunisia .
The Gaoligong pika ( Ochotona gaoligongensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Benthophilus pinchuki , Pinchuk 's pugolovka , is a species of gobiid fish found along the eastern and western coasts of the Caspian Sea , but absent on the middle part .
Antidesma ghaesembilla is a species of plant in the family Phyllanthaceae .
Micropolypodium is a genus of ferns in the family Polypodiaceae .
Catasetum planiceps is a species of orchid found from North South America to Brazil .
Argyrosauridae is a family of large titanosaurian dinosaurs known from the late Cretaceous period of Argentina and Egypt .
Nannostomus eques , commonly known as the diptail or brown pencilfish , is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the Lebiasinidae family of characins .
Pholidocarpus macrocarpus is a species of flowering plant in the family Arecaceae .
Viola frank - smithii is a rare species of violet known by the common name Frank Smith 's violet .
Mahavisaurus is an extinct genus of rhytidosteid temnospondyl from the early Triassic period ( Induan stage ) of Iraro , Madagascar .
Eleutherodactylus guanahacabibes is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Cuba , and is named for the Guanahacabibes Peninsula .
Eriogonum fasciculatum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names California buckwheat and Eastern Mojave buckwheat .
Microstigmata is a genus of spiders in South Africa .
The species is named in honour of Mr. Jari - Pekka Kaitila , who was the first to recognize that the specimens representing Teleiodes kaitilai , are not conspecific with Teleiodes saltuum .
Dryopteris arguta , with the common name coastal woodfern , is a species of wood fern .
Croton guatemalensis , known as Copalchi , is a plant species of the genus Croton .
The Sumatran shrewlike mouse ( Mus crociduroides ) is a species of mouse .
Glycymeris decussata , or the decussate bittersweet , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Glycymerididae .
Paraspirifer is a genus of large brachiopods ( up to about 7.5 centimetres or 3.0 inches ) that lived during the late Lower and Middle Devonian in what now are Germany , Spain , Morocco and the United States ( New York State and Ohio ) .
Sagittaria rigida , the sessilefruit arrowhead or Canadian arrowhead , is an aquatic plant species native to Canada and to the United States and also naturalized in Great Britain .
Amphisbaena heathi , also known as Heath 's worm lizard , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Dinapate wrightii , also known as the Giant Palm Borer , is the largest species in the beetle family Bostrichidae , and sometimes a pest of palm trees , especially Washingtonia filifera and Washingtonia robusta .
Emblemaria diphyodontis , the Venezuelan blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Cubagua Island , Venezuela , in the western Atlantic ocean .
Ceratomantis yunnanensis is a species of praying mantis native to China that was undiscovered until 1986 .
Camellia chrysantha , the golden camellia , is a species of plant in the Theaceae family .
Struthiolaria papulosa , common name the `` ostrich foot snail '' or `` ostrich foot shell '' , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Struthiolariidae .
Caecum armoricum , common name the DeFolin 's lagoon snail , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Caecidae .
Ericusa fulgetrum , the Lightning Volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
The Bahir 's fan - throated lizard ( Sitana bahiri ) is an endemic species of agamid lizard recently found from Sri Lanka .
Schinopsis brasiliensis is a species of flowering plant in the cashew family known by the common names baraúna or braúna , quebracho , and chamacoco .
Bondarzewia is a widely distributed genus of fungi in the family Bondarzewiaceae .
Marina parryi is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Parry 's false prairie - clover .
Bossiaea bracteosa , commonly known as mountain leafless bossiaea , is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae .
Cylindrocline is a genus of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
The genus is monospecific , and the single species is Pedinella hexacostata Vysotskij .
Hesperomeles obtusifolia is a species of plant native to South America .
Aeranthes , abbreviated Aerth in the horticultural trade , is an orchid genus with 47 species , mostly from shady , tropical humid forests in Zimbabwe , Madagascar and islands in the Western Indian Ocean .
Allium abbasii is a species of onion native to Iran .
Paconius corniculatus is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Paconius .
Scaphiophis is a genus of African snakes .
The Bactrodinae are a small subfamily of the reduviid ( assassin bugs ) .
Bihunichthys monopteroides is a species of spineless eel native to Indonesia & Malaysia .
Vallonia suevica is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial , pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Valloniidae .
Caprimulgus is a large and very widespread genus of nightjars , medium - sized nocturnal birds with long pointed wings , short legs and short bills .
Gregariella coralliophaga , or the artist 's mussel , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae .
Epiphyllum crenatum , the Crenate Orchid Cactus , is a species of cactus and one of the most important parents in creating the Epiphyllum - hybrids commonly cultivated throughout the world .
Crangonoidea is a superfamily of shrimp containing the two families Crangonidae and Glyphocrangonidae .
Palaeoniscum is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish from the Permian period of Europe and North America .
The Chinese bush warbler ( Locustella tacsanowskia ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Streptanthus gracilis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name alpine jewelflower .
Orsonwelles graphicus is a species of linyphiid spider endemic to the Big Island of Hawaii .
Styelidae is a family of ascidian tunicates .
Diictodon was a genus of therapsid , roughly 45 cm ( 18 inches ) long .
Pleurobema sintoxia , common name the Round Pigtoe , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Pastilla dacuna is a species of freshwater crab in the family Parathelphusidae .
Dichoptera is a genus of plant - hoppers found in tropical Asia .
The Megophryidae ( commonly known as the litter frogs ) are a large family of frogs native to the warm southeast of Asia , from the Himalayan foothills eastwards , south to Indonesia and the Greater Sunda Islands in Maritime Southeast Asia , and extending to the Philippines .
Atelopus onorei is a small species of bright yellow and green toad in the family Bufonidae .
It was formerly treated as a subspecies of the white - crested laughingthrush ( G. leucolophus ) , but unlike that species the plumage of the Sumatran laughingthrush is blackish - brown and white .
Anelosimus pratchetti is a species of tangle - web spider found in New South Wales , Australia .
The genus Catopsbaatar was named by Zofia Kielan - Jaworowska in 1974 and 1994 based on a single species .
Fejervarya triora is a species of frog belonging to the family Dicroglossidae .
Peritrichocera tsilaosa is a species of moth in the Carposinidae family .
Citrus wintersii , the Brown River finger lime , is a plant species native to the Brown River region in Papua - New Guinea .
Oryzomys peninsulae , also known as the Lower California rice rat , is a species of rodent from western Mexico .
Xenocalamus bicolor , or the slender quill - snouted snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Phronima sedentaria is a species of amphipod crustacean found in oceans at a depth of up to 1 km ( 0.6 mi ) .
Simolestes ( meaning `` hearkening thief '' ) is an extinct pliosaurid genus that lived in the Middle to Late Jurassic .
Sanicula tuberosa is a species of flowering plant in the parsley family known by the common name turkey pea .
Eriogonum baileyi is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Bailey 's buckwheat .
Borojevia tetrapodifera is a species of calcareous sponge in the genus Borojevia from New Zealand .
Trachycarpus is a genus of nine species of palms native to Asia , from the Himalaya east to eastern China .
Ucides is a genus of mangrove crabs in the monotypic family Ucididae , containing two species :
Parhecyra costata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parhecyra .
Eotitanosuchidae is an extinct family of biarmosuchian therapsids .
The African lungfishes are the genus Protopterus and constitute the four species of lungfish found in Africa .
Antrimpos is an extinct genus of crustacean which existed during the Triassic and Jurassic periods .
Steindachnerina is a genus of toothless characins from South America , with 24 currently described species :
Melpomene brevipes is a species of fern in the Polypodiaceae family .
The Thermoanaerobacteraceae is a highly polyphyletic family of bacteria placed within the class clostridia .
Petrocephalus arnegardi is a species of electric fish in the genus Petrocephalus native to the Central Congo River basin .
It contains a single species , Yurgovuchia doellingi .
Albizia canescens , commonly known as Belmont Siris , is a species of Albizia , endemic to Northern Australia .
Pyropelta wakefieldi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyropeltidae .
Vesperus serranoi is a species of beetle in the Vesperidae family that is endemic to the Iberian Peninsula .
Aralosaurus ( meaning `` Aral Sea lizard '' , because it was found in the Aral Sea - Greek sauros = lizard ) was a genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur which lived during the Late Cretaceous of what is now Kazakhstan .
The plant species Musa ingens is the physically largest member of the family Musaceae .
Hierodula patellifera , common name giant Asian mantis , Asian mantis or Indochina mantis , is a species of praying mantis belonging to genus Hierodula .
Liotyphlops beui is a species of nonvenomous snake in the Anomalepididae family .
Carex lasiocarpa is a species of sedge known by the common names slender sedge and woollyfruit sedge .
Mesonauta festivus , the flag cichlid , is a species of cichlid native to tropical rivers in Brazil , Peru , Paraguay and Bolivia .
The Inyangani river frog ( Amietia inyangae ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Goodwin 's broad - clawed shrew ( Cryptotis goodwini ) is a species of mammal in the Soricidae ( Shrew ) family .
Cruxicheiros ( meaning `` cross hand '' ) is a genus of tetanuran theropod dinosaur which lived in the Middle Jurassic of England .
Myrmica specioides is a species of ant of the genus Myrmica .
Nebria testacea is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Greece and Turkey .
Frasera ( green gentian ) is a genus in the gentian family , native to North America and named for John Fraser , a Scottish botanist and colleague of Thomas Walter .
Trichacalolepta mouhoti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichacalolepta .
Delphinium hansenii is a species of larkspur known by the common names Eldorado larkspur and Hansen 's delphinium .
Agonum texanum is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily , that is endemic to Texas , United States .
Triphysaria eriantha is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family , known by the common names johnny - tuck and butter - and - eggs .
The Lestidae are a rather small family of cosmopolitan , large - sized , slender damselflies known commonly as the spreadwings or spread - winged damselflies .
Heronia is a monotypic Neotropical genus of skippers in the subfamily Eudaminae .
Helianthus ciliaris is a species of sunflower known by the common names Texas blueweed and yerba parda .
Calosoma maderae is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae which is 25 - -35 millimetres ( 0.98 - -1.38 in ) long .
Bycanistes is a genus of medium to large , primarily frugivorous hornbills ( family Bucerotidae ) found in the forests and woodlands of Sub - Saharan Africa .
Scorzoneroides autumnalis , commonly called autumn hawkbit , is a perennial plant species , widespread in its native range in Eurasia ( from Europe east to western Siberia ) , and introduced in North America .
Orogenia fusiformis is a species of flowering plants in the carrot family known by the common name California Indian potato .
Geastrum quadrifidum , commonly known as the rayed earthstar or four - footed earthstar , is an inedible species of mushroom belonging to the genus Geastrum , or earthstar fungi .
Calopadia editae is a species of lichen in the family Pilocarpaceae .
The type species , Fulengia youngi , was described by Carroll and Galton in 1977 .
Quararibea is a genus of aromatic plants in the family Malvaceae .
Gobius tropicus is a species of fish currently classified in the Gobiidae family .
Clinus helenae , the Helen 's klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean around South Africa where it is a denizen of tide pools .
Bartholomea annulata is a species of sea anemone in the family Aiptasiidae , commonly known as the ringed anemone or corkscrew anemone .
Hypsoblennius caulopus , the Tidepool blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern Pacific ocean .
Rehmannia elata ( Chinese foxglove ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Orobanchaceae , native to China .
Threadfins are silvery grey perciform marine fish of the family Polynemidae .
Silverstoneia nubicola ( Boquete rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Astelia is a genus of rhizomatous tufted perennials in the family Asteliaceae which are native to various island in the Pacific , Indian , and South Atlantic Oceans , as well as to Australia and to the southernmost tip of South America .
Allium punctum is a species of wild onion known by the common name dotted onion or Modoc onion .
Pantolambda is an extinct genus of Paleocene pantodont mammal .
Dasycnemia naparimalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Dasycnemia .
Viola oahuensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the violet family known by the common name Oahu violet .
Ranunculus asiaticus ( Persian buttercup ) is a species of buttercup ( Ranunculus ) native to the eastern Mediterranean region in southwestern Asia , southeastern Europe ( Crete , Karpathos and Rhodes ) , and northeastern Africa .
Monopsis is a genus of small , Lobelia - like herbaceous plants indigenous to Africa .
Quercus glauca ( syn . Cyclobalanopsis glauca ) , also known as ring - cupped oak , Japanese blue oak or glaucous - leaf oak , is an Asian species in the genus Quercus in the beech family .
Parapithecidae is an extinct family of primates which lived in the Eocene and Oligocene periods in Egypt .
Silvaroo is a genus of megafaunal macropods that existed in Australia in the Pleistocene .
Fluvidona orphana is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Hydrobiidae .
Megacephala crucigera is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Macleay in 1863 , and is endemic to Australia .
Phasmahyla cochranae , sometimes called the chocolatefoot leaf frog , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Thelesperma pubescens is a species of flowering plants in the aster family known by the common names hairy greenthread and Uinta greenthread .
Side - blotched lizards are lizards of the genus Uta .
Armillaria luteobubalina , commonly known as the Australian honey fungus , is a species of mushroom in the family Physalacriaceae .
Gymnocranius is a genus of emperors native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Coelogyne usitana is a species of orchid discovered in the late 1990s .
Opomyza florum , common name Yellow Cereal Fly or Grass Fly , is a species of acalyptrate Diptera .
Coronula diadema is a species of whale barnacle only known to live on humpback whales , and also possibly sperm whales and finback whales .
Cariua sulphurea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cariua .
Paratriaenops pauliani is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Lupinus diffusus ( Oak Ridge lupine , spreading lupine , or sky - blue lupine ) is a species of lupine native to the southeastern United States , from North Carolina south to Florida and west to Mississippi .
The Colorado River cutthroat trout ( Oncorhynchus clarki pleuriticus ) is a subspecies of cutthroat trout native only to the Green and Colorado River basins , which are west of the Continental Divide .
Agyneta birulaioides is a species of sheet weaver found in Ukraine , Kazakhstan , Russia and Mongolia .
Allopaa is a small genus of frogs in the family Dicroglossidae .
The Brachyceran family Vermileonidae ( the sole member of the infraorder Vermileonomorpha ) is a small family of uncertain affinities and unusual biology , containing fewer than 80 rare species in 10 genera .
Guaduella is a genus of African plants in the grass family , the only genus in the tribe Guaduellieae .
Subarchaeopacha alberici is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Subarchaeopacha .
Duthieastrum is a genus of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae .
Collilongus ( meaning `` long neck '' ) is an extinct genus of small archosauriform , possibly a rauisuchian , known from Early Triassic ( Olenekian age ) rocks of Czatkowice 1 , Poland .
Dracoraptor is a genus of carnivorous neotheropod dinosaur from the Hettangian age of the Early Jurassic period of Wales .
Brownleea is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to Africa and Madagascar .
Petrophytum ( orth . var . Petrophyton ) is a small genus of plants in the rose family known as the rock spiraeas or rockmats .
Nemacheilus dori is a species of ray - finned fish in the Balitoridae family .
Mitra pudica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Meganthribus pupa is a species of beetles belonging to the Anthribidae family .
Anhanguera piscator ( meaning `` fishing old devil '' ) is a species of pterosaur known from the Early Cretaceous ( Aptian age , 112Ma ) Santana Formation of Brazil .
Tetraliidae is a family of crabs .
Adelophryne gutturosa ( common name : Guiana Shield frog ) is a species of frog in the family Eleutherodactylidae ( formerly in Leptodactylidae ) .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Pseudolasiobolus minutissimus , described by German mycologist Reinhard Agerer in 1983 .
Melica uniflora , commonly known as wood melick , is a species of grass in the family Poaceae that is native to much of Europe , and to parts of South West Asia and North Africa .
Trematocara macrostoma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is known from the southern portion of the lake .
Crudia zeylanica was a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Batrachosuchus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Triassic of South Africa .
Rumex salicifolius is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common names willow dock and willow - leaved dock .
Amblygobius sphynx or the Sphinx goby is a species of goby found in brackish and salt water in Thailand .
Garcinia echinocarpa is a species of small to medium tree in the Clusiaceae family .
Urocitellus is a genus of ground squirrels .
Castilleja brevistyla is a species of Castilleja ( Indian paintbrush ) known by the common name shortstyle Indian paintbrush .
Chasmanthium latifolium , known as Woodoats , Inland sea oats , Northern sea oats , and River oats is a grass native to the central and eastern United States , Manitoba , and northeastern Mexico ; it grows as far north as Pennsylvania and Michigan , where it is a threatened species .
Pycnanthemum californicum is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Sierra mint .
Tritoxa ra is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Tritoxa of the family Ulidiidae .
Micrixalus silvaticus is a species of frog in the Micrixalidae family .
Lasiophrys latifrons is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lasiophrys .
Merica asperella , common name the elegant nutmeg , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Morus serrata , known as Himalayan mulberry , is a species of mulberry native to the Himalaya and the mountains of southwestern China , at altitudes of up to 2300 m. It is a small deciduous tree growing to 15 m tall .
Dendropanax colombianus , Mano de Oso , is an important habitat to many bird species , and promotes the settlement of other important plants such as Cedro tree ( Cedrela montana ) and Chuwacá tree ( Prunus buxifolia ) , which the subsequent reforestation in the sub - páramo .
Asterropteryx ensifera , known commonly as the Miller 's Damsel , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
Manicina areolata , commonly known as rose coral , is a colonial species of stony coral in the family Mussidae .
Trichopeza albocincta , is a European species of Empididae .
Lasiurus is the genus comprising hairy - tailed bats .
Ophryotrocha craigsmithi is a species of polychaete worm .
Aubrieta deltoidea is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family .
Eriocheir is a genus of crabs , including the Chinese mitten crab , E. sinensis .
The only species is Pararhadinaea melanogaster , sometimes known as the Madagascar burrowing snake .
Varanops is an extinct genus of Early Permian varanopid synapsid known from Texas and Oklahoma of the United States .
Streptomyces alkalithermotolerans is a alkaliphilic and thermotolerant bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from the Lonar soda lake in India .
Epiplatys sexfasciatus or six - barred panchax is a species of African rivuline that can be found in West Africa .
Notogramma cimiciformis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Notogramma of the family Ulidiidae .
Olivella columellaris is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olivellidae , the dwarf olives .
Cyathophorum bulbosum , commonly known as the false fern - moss , is a species of moss in the family Hypopterygiaceae .
Oxobacter is a genus of Gram - positive obligately anaerobic rod - shaped acetogenic bacteria .
Cyphotilapia is a small genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Tanganyika , with C. frontosa being roughly confined to the northern half of the lake and C. gibberosa being roughly confined to the southern half of the lake .
Navarretia nigelliformis is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name adobe navarretia .
Erigeron muirii ( Muir 's fleabane ) is a rare Arctic species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Potamonautes didieri is a species of crab in the family Potamonautidae .
Faradaya is a genus of plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1865 .
Sabal bermudana , commonly known as the Bermuda palmetto or bibby - tree , is one of 15 species of palm trees in the genus Sabal and is endemic to Bermuda although reportedly naturalized in the Leeward Islands .
Parrotiopsis jacquemontiana is a species of deciduous shrub or small tree in the witch hazel family , native to the western Himalayas , particularly Kashmir , Murree , Hazara , the Swat District , and Kurram , at altitudes from 1200 to 2800 meters .
Echinochimaera is an extinct genus of fish , it was assigned to the order chimaera by Jack Sepkoski in 2002 .
Solidago roanensis , the Roan Mountain goldenrod , is a North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .
The only described species Malloneta guineensis is endemic to West Africa .
Alstroemeria pulchella is a South American species of flowering plant in the family Alstroemeriaceae .
Callipogon relictus is a species of longhorn beetle which is mostly found in the southern part of Russian Far East , but also in China and Korea .
Eumetula pulla is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Newtoniellidae .
Helianthus maximiliani is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name Maximilian sunflower .
Cleomella plocasperma is a species of flowering plant in the cleome family known by the common name twisted cleomella and alkali stinkweed .
Calotomus viridescens , commonly known as the viridescent- or dotted parrotfish , is a species of parrotfish native to the waters of the Maldives , and Red Sea , from the Gulf of Aqaba to south to the Chagos Archipelago .
Fritillaria ussuriensis is an Asian species of herbaceous plant in the lily family , native to Korea , the Primorye Region of Russia , and northeastern China ( Heilongjiang , Jilin , Liaoning ) .
Oncidium longipes is a species of orchid occurring from Brazil to northeastern Argentina .
Chrysolina is a large genus of leaf beetles in the subfamily Chrysomelinae .
Thalassocyon tui is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Ficidae , the fig shells .
The Durango mud turtle ( Kinosternon durangoense ) is a species of mud turtle in the Kinosternidae family endemic to Mexico .
Pterophyllum is a small genus of freshwater fish from the family Cichlidae known to most aquarists as `` angelfish '' .
Brachionostylum is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Brachionostylum pullei .
Eucephalus gormanii is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Gorman 's aster .
Aechmea maculata is an evergreen plant species in the family Bromeliaceae and the genus Aechmea .
Cyrtillus albofasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cyrtillus .
Polypedates megacephalus , the Hong Kong Whipping Frog or Spot - legged Tree Frog , is a species in the shrub frog family ( Rhacophoridae ) .
Phlyctaeniidae is an extinct family of placoderm fishes that lived during the Devonian period , mainly in Norway and North America .
Horabagridae is a family of catfishes containing two genera , Horabagrus and Pseudeutropius .
Chaenactis douglasii is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Douglas ' dustymaiden .
Ulmus laevis var . parvifolia is a mutant variety of European White Elm found exclusively on the island of Ada Ciganlija , in the Sava at Belgrade , Serbia .
The Asian grass lizard , six - striped long - tailed lizard , or long - tailed grass lizard ( Takydromus sexlineatus ) is an arboreal , diurnal species of lizard .
Pamparaptor is an extinct genus of carnivorous deinonychosaur from the late Cretaceous period .
Abramites is a genus of headstanders that occurs in South America .
Odostomia crassicosta , common name the thick - ribbed pyramid - shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
A single species is recognized , Glyptoteles leucacrinella .
Dikelocephalidae is a family of trilobites , that lived during the Upper Cambrian .

Heteroclinus tristis , the Sharp - nose weedfish , is a species of clinid native to the coastal waters of southern Australia where it prefers sandy reefs with sparse vegetation .
Afzelia is a genus in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae of the family Fabaceae ( legumes ) .
Acer wuyuanense is a species of maple tree in the soapberry family .
Artanema longifolium is an edible flowering plant species found in tropical Africa , India and South - East Asia .
Acromantis gestri , common name Sumatran Acromantis or Thailand boxer praying mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Malaysia and Sumatra .
Nimbochromis polystigma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi , in the Great Rift Valley system of Africa .
Zephyranthes insularum H.H.Hume ex Moldenke ( i.e. the species named by Hume ) is accepted by the World Checklist of Selected Plant Families as a distinct species .
The †Raphistomatidae is a taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , Paleozoic marine gastropod mollusks .
Allium macrum , the rock onion , is an American species of wild onion native to the eastern and central parts of the US States of Oregon and Washington .
Cyperus squarrosus is a species of sedge known by several common names , including bearded flatsedge and awned flatsedge .
Aepisaurus ( /ˌiːpɨˈsɔrəs/ ; derived from the Greek : αἰπεινός - ' lofty / high ' and σαυρος - ' lizard ' , i.e. `` lofty lizard '' ) was a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Albian - age Lower Cretaceous Grès vert of Départment du Vaucluse , France , around 100 million years ago .
Shafera is a genus of plants in the groundsel tribe within the sunflower family .
Euselates cineracea is a species of beetle belonging to the family Scarabaeidae .

Aequipecten acanthodes , or the thistle scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Volutospina is an extinct genus of fossil gastropod that lived from the Cretaceous to the Eocene in Africa , Asia , Europe , North America , and South America .
Corythoichthys is a genus of pipefishes of the family Syngnathidae .
Ophioglossum californicum , known by the common name California adder 's tongue , is an uncommon species of fern in the family Ophioglossaceae .
Leptotyphlops affinis , or the Venezuela blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Ark clam is the common name for a family of small to large - sized saltwater clams or marine bivalve molluscs in the family Arcidae .
Cotoneaster horizontalis is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cotoneaster of the family Rosaceae , native to western China .

Titanoeca quadriguttata is a species of spider in the family Titanoecidae .
Sagittaria macrophylla , common name papa de agua , is an aquatic plant species endemic to central Mexico ( States of Jalisco , Michoacán , México , Hidalgo , and the Distrito Federal ) , primarily in the region close to the nation 's capital .
Anabarilius xundianensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus , that is endemic to China .
Oregoniidae is a family of crabs , formerly included in the family Majidae .
The White - pinion Spotted ( Lomographa bimaculata ) is a geometer moth species ( family Geometridae ) .

Ampullaria bicarinata is an extinct species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae .

Dyckia ferruginea is a plant species in the genus Dyckia .
Belonoglanis tenuis is a species of loach catfish found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo and the Republic of Congo where it occurs in the Congo River basin .
Ficimia publia ( common name : blotched hooknose snake ) is a species of colubrid snake , indigenous to southern Mexico ( Yucatan , Jalisco , and Morelos ) , Belize , Guatemala , and Honduras .
Hexanematichthys is a genus of sea catfishes consisting of three species .
The Mindanao racket - tail ( Prioniturus waterstradti ) is a species of parrot in the Psittaculidae family .
Nippia alboscutellata is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Nippia of the family Tephritidae .
Lysimachia hybrida , common name Mississippi loosestrife or lowland yellow loosestrife , is a plant species widespread in much of the United States and Canada , absent only from the deserts in the west and the Arctic and sub - Arctic regions of the far north .
Paraphemone multimaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraphemone .
Entimus imperialis , common name Brazilian Diamond Beetle , is a species of broad - nosed weevils belonging to the family true weevil and the Entiminae subfamily .
Anne Schwanewilms ( born 1967 , in Gelsenkirchen , West Germany ) is a German lyric soprano .
